1
00:00:00,195 --> 00:00:01,964
(Kim Jae Won...)

2
00:00:01,965 --> 00:00:04,435
(and Boom...)

3
00:00:04,895 --> 00:00:06,805
(join 2 Days 1 Night's real winter special.)

4
00:00:07,835 --> 00:00:09,734
(It's minus 17°C in Inje.)

5
00:00:09,735 --> 00:00:12,145
(The 2026 Real Winter Reboot)

6
00:00:12,445 --> 00:00:14,745
(The landscape is barren...)

7
00:00:15,645 --> 00:00:18,145
(and they're so exhausted they could pass out.)

8
00:00:19,045 --> 00:00:22,385
(They must resort to anything to survive.)

9
00:00:23,055 --> 00:00:24,915
(However...)

10
00:00:25,355 --> 00:00:27,625
(Boom and Jae Won must leave for prior engagements.)

11
00:00:28,155 --> 00:00:29,825
(Only us five sleep here.)

12
00:00:30,625 --> 00:00:33,325
(They have one last chance to avoid sleeping outdoors...)

13
00:00:33,665 --> 00:00:35,265
(in the dismal cold.)

14
00:00:36,435 --> 00:00:38,865
(They are more desperate than ever.)

15
00:00:40,565 --> 00:00:42,775
(They are more sincere than ever.)

16
00:00:43,305 --> 00:00:46,345
(Who gets to sleep indoors?)

17
00:00:47,305 --> 00:00:50,545
(Lee Joon will sleep indoors.)

18
00:00:51,245 --> 00:00:53,615
(He's the happiest right now.)

19
00:00:54,085 --> 00:00:57,005
(Meanwhile, the outdoor sleepers are braving the minus 20°C temperature.)

20
00:00:57,315 --> 00:01:00,485
(They're worried if they can sleep at all.)

21
00:01:00,925 --> 00:01:03,925
(Will we survive and see each other in the morning?)

22
00:01:05,195 --> 00:01:08,265
(2 Days 1 Night)

23
00:01:08,725 --> 00:01:10,634
(The real winter night was long, )

24
00:01:10,635 --> 00:01:13,105
(but morning has come.)

25
00:01:17,635 --> 00:01:21,045
(Day 2 of the real winter trip)

26
00:01:22,005 --> 00:01:25,475
(Joon starts the day with a stretch.)

27
00:01:26,185 --> 00:01:28,485
(In a daze)

28
00:01:29,055 --> 00:01:31,955
(He dresses warmly.)

29
00:01:33,025 --> 00:01:35,525
(Then he folds his bedding.)

30
00:01:36,825 --> 00:01:39,965
(Joon's up and ready at 7:20am.)

31
00:01:40,625 --> 00:01:42,735
(Puffy face)

32
00:01:43,365 --> 00:01:45,765
(It's obvious he slept well.)

33
00:01:47,035 --> 00:01:48,035
(They slept out here?)

34
00:01:48,036 --> 00:01:49,535
How did they manage? Are they dead?

35
00:01:50,635 --> 00:01:51,635
It's freezing cold.

36
00:01:51,636 --> 00:01:53,505
(He feels the cold with each step.)

37
00:01:54,705 --> 00:01:56,144
(A cold wave alert was issued...)

38
00:01:56,145 --> 00:01:58,245
(on January 3, the day of the shoot.)

39
00:01:58,645 --> 00:02:01,185
(Current temperature: minus 13°C)

40
00:02:01,845 --> 00:02:05,655
(The base camp is frozen solid.)

41
00:02:06,525 --> 00:02:09,095
(Is everyone okay?)

42
00:02:09,725 --> 00:02:12,155
(Walking over)

43
00:02:13,065 --> 00:02:14,124
(A large pot?)

44
00:02:14,125 --> 00:02:15,365
(Looking very suspicious)

45
00:02:16,095 --> 00:02:19,005
(He strikes a solemn pose.)

46
00:02:20,105 --> 00:02:22,875
(Suddenly, he strikes the pot.)

47
00:02:22,975 --> 00:02:26,305
Okay.

48
00:02:26,575 --> 00:02:29,345
It's time to wake up.

49
00:02:30,115 --> 00:02:33,414
(He's the morning angel.)

50
00:02:33,415 --> 00:02:36,355
Morning has come.

51
00:02:37,115 --> 00:02:38,355
Are they all dead?

52
00:02:39,125 --> 00:02:40,225
Last night...

53
00:02:41,125 --> 00:02:44,155
(He can't even hear breathing.)

54
00:02:44,725 --> 00:02:46,165
No one's getting up.

55
00:02:46,895 --> 00:02:48,495
- Seriously?
- Seriously.

56
00:02:49,595 --> 00:02:51,364
(What is happening?)

57
00:02:51,365 --> 00:02:52,365
Hang on.

58
00:02:54,635 --> 00:02:56,605
(Just then)

59
00:02:57,505 --> 00:02:58,774
(Se Yoon thaws, fortunately.)

60
00:02:58,775 --> 00:02:59,805
What now?

61
00:03:01,305 --> 00:03:02,745
Wake up.

62
00:03:05,115 --> 00:03:07,815
(Sudden bad breath attack)

63
00:03:08,445 --> 00:03:10,555
- Se Yoon's acting a bit weird.
- Is he?

64
00:03:12,155 --> 00:03:13,685
I feel really bad now.

65
00:03:14,055 --> 00:03:15,695
The fire... It burned out.

66
00:03:16,755 --> 00:03:19,125
(All that's left are the ashes.)

67
00:03:19,495 --> 00:03:20,995
The wood is frozen too.

68
00:03:21,665 --> 00:03:22,834
The firewood...

69
00:03:22,835 --> 00:03:24,635
(The cold froze even the firewood.)

70
00:03:25,265 --> 00:03:27,905
(Se Yoon escapes the tent.)

71
00:03:28,435 --> 00:03:31,035
(Crawling)

72
00:03:31,305 --> 00:03:32,404
There's a survivor.

73
00:03:32,405 --> 00:03:33,775
(Sounds pleased)

74
00:03:34,545 --> 00:03:36,175
Congratulations.

75
00:03:37,045 --> 00:03:38,445
You survived.

76
00:03:39,845 --> 00:03:43,455
(He took the brunt of the cold.)

77
00:03:44,085 --> 00:03:46,084
(Finally, at last.)

78
00:03:46,085 --> 00:03:47,184
He's alive!

79
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:48,324
(His back straightens.)

80
00:03:48,325 --> 00:03:49,355
Congratulations.

81
00:03:50,755 --> 00:03:53,025
(I survived!)

82
00:03:53,595 --> 00:03:54,665
(Laughing)

83
00:03:56,465 --> 00:03:59,864
(While Se Yoon thaws out, )

84
00:03:59,865 --> 00:04:00,865
I'm impressed.

85
00:04:00,866 --> 00:04:02,474
(DinDin...)

86
00:04:02,475 --> 00:04:05,135
(and Seon Ho wake up too.)

87
00:04:05,635 --> 00:04:08,005
(I'm thirsty.)

88
00:04:09,475 --> 00:04:11,015
It's like we're in a fridge.

89
00:04:12,075 --> 00:04:13,285
What is this?

90
00:04:14,345 --> 00:04:15,645
What is this?

91
00:04:16,215 --> 00:04:17,614
(The water is frozen solid.)

92
00:04:17,615 --> 00:04:19,325
How are we to deal with this?

93
00:04:19,985 --> 00:04:21,424
Water should be drinkable.

94
00:04:21,425 --> 00:04:22,895
(Everything is frozen.)

95
00:04:23,555 --> 00:04:24,594
My gosh.

96
00:04:24,595 --> 00:04:25,864
(They hurry to light a fire.)

97
00:04:25,865 --> 00:04:26,895
Hey, this...

98
00:04:27,725 --> 00:04:29,165
It looks scary, even.

99
00:04:30,035 --> 00:04:31,164
It's frozen stiff.

100
00:04:31,165 --> 00:04:32,464
(The butane gas canister is covered in frost.)

101
00:04:32,465 --> 00:04:34,935
Bring boxes or something. Let's start a fire.

102
00:04:35,105 --> 00:04:36,204
Leave it there.

103
00:04:36,205 --> 00:04:37,981
(The other members are trying to rekindle the fire.)

104
00:04:38,005 --> 00:04:40,474
Did the eldest member fail to get up?

105
00:04:40,475 --> 00:04:41,505
Oh, right.

106
00:04:41,875 --> 00:04:43,074
- Wait.
- What's Jong Min doing?

107
00:04:43,075 --> 00:04:45,745
(Jong Min's absence has been forgotten.)

108
00:04:46,445 --> 00:04:47,584
It's not working.

109
00:04:47,585 --> 00:04:50,385
(Jong Min, I'm coming to you!)

110
00:04:51,055 --> 00:04:53,625
(Looking pitiful)

111
00:04:53,955 --> 00:04:55,524
Jong Min.

112
00:04:55,525 --> 00:04:56,725
He's still alive.

113
00:04:56,995 --> 00:04:58,254
Hey, I'm melting now.

114
00:04:58,255 --> 00:05:00,695
(I'm melting now.)

115
00:05:00,995 --> 00:05:02,994
Really? Were you getting defrosted?

116
00:05:02,995 --> 00:05:04,035
Yes.

117
00:05:04,835 --> 00:05:06,805
Jong Min, you must go back to your family.

118
00:05:07,435 --> 00:05:09,305
You survived the night at minus 40°C, right?

119
00:05:09,505 --> 00:05:11,775
We're just barely breathing. That's it.

120
00:05:12,405 --> 00:05:13,945
Congratulations on making it.

121
00:05:15,105 --> 00:05:17,045
The air was the worst I'd experienced.

122
00:05:17,175 --> 00:05:18,715
- What?
- It was the chilliest.

123
00:05:19,185 --> 00:05:20,545
I'm glad that I'm still breathing.

124
00:05:20,985 --> 00:05:22,145
- We somehow survived.
- Yes.

125
00:05:23,715 --> 00:05:24,884
Gosh, it was a harsh night.

126
00:05:24,885 --> 00:05:26,285
Last night was the toughest.

127
00:05:27,025 --> 00:05:29,025
- Was it in the top five?
- Yes.

128
00:05:29,125 --> 00:05:30,354
- It was in the top five.
- Last night had to be...

129
00:05:30,355 --> 00:05:31,955
- one of the toughest nights.
- Totally.

130
00:05:32,325 --> 00:05:33,494
We weren't underwater.

131
00:05:33,495 --> 00:05:35,055
But it sure felt like I was underwater.

132
00:05:36,395 --> 00:05:37,635
But somehow, we did it.

133
00:05:38,065 --> 00:05:39,464
- Yes.
- It's morning again.

134
00:05:39,465 --> 00:05:40,635
Right. We somehow did it.

135
00:05:40,905 --> 00:05:43,935
I remembered the famous saying, "This shall pass too."

136
00:05:44,905 --> 00:05:46,144
What are we doing now?

137
00:05:46,145 --> 00:05:47,645
Can't we go home?

138
00:05:48,145 --> 00:05:49,644
How much longer must we stay here?

139
00:05:49,645 --> 00:05:50,715
(Please let us go home.)

140
00:05:50,945 --> 00:05:52,045
We...

141
00:05:52,415 --> 00:05:53,614
- What?
- What is it?

142
00:05:53,615 --> 00:05:55,361
- What's going on?
- We prepared one last activity.

143
00:05:55,385 --> 00:05:57,084
Through a small game...

144
00:05:57,085 --> 00:05:58,485
What? This sounds like a big one.

145
00:05:58,885 --> 00:05:59,924
- His facial expression seems off.
- we'll pick a member...

146
00:05:59,925 --> 00:06:00,925
whose back will be splashed with water.

147
00:06:00,926 --> 00:06:02,525
- What did you say?
- At minus 15°C?

148
00:06:02,655 --> 00:06:04,094
- Have you gone mad?
- Gosh, stop it.

149
00:06:04,095 --> 00:06:05,095
The water just might freeze.

150
00:06:05,096 --> 00:06:06,795
- Are you serious?
- Stop it.

151
00:06:07,395 --> 00:06:09,194
(Everything has frozen this morning...)

152
00:06:09,195 --> 00:06:11,665
(as the temperature is at minus 15°C.)

153
00:06:11,865 --> 00:06:14,364
- You should do it with us then.
- This will give us a shock.

154
00:06:14,365 --> 00:06:15,365
- Oh, this...
- Joon.

155
00:06:15,366 --> 00:06:17,334
- Hey. The water will be icy cold.
- Take this one for the team.

156
00:06:17,335 --> 00:06:18,335
It will freeze.

157
00:06:18,336 --> 00:06:19,844
This is why you work out.

158
00:06:19,845 --> 00:06:21,405
- No.
- What?

159
00:06:21,775 --> 00:06:24,275
It's the grand finale of the Real Winter Training Center.

160
00:06:24,845 --> 00:06:26,045
A water splash down your back.

161
00:06:26,815 --> 00:06:27,844
That sounds fun.

162
00:06:27,845 --> 00:06:29,925
You'll play the game to pick only one member for it.

163
00:06:30,055 --> 00:06:32,315
(The last journey in this brutal cold)

164
00:06:32,525 --> 00:06:34,185
A water splash now could kill us.

165
00:06:35,485 --> 00:06:36,524
(Bringing in a board with nails)

166
00:06:36,525 --> 00:06:37,725
I'm so nervous.

167
00:06:40,025 --> 00:06:41,694
We prepared five nails.

168
00:06:41,695 --> 00:06:43,165
(The 5 nails are placed 2cm apart.)

169
00:06:43,665 --> 00:06:45,635
- You'll hammer the nails in order.
- Okay.

170
00:06:46,565 --> 00:06:48,334
If you manage to hammer the nail, you've succeeded.

171
00:06:48,335 --> 00:06:50,505
- Just 1 member?
- Just 1 member.

172
00:06:51,175 --> 00:06:52,745
It's the deciding moment.

173
00:06:53,575 --> 00:06:55,374
Let's play rock-paper-scissors to decide who will go first.

174
00:06:55,375 --> 00:06:56,645
The order will be crucial.

175
00:06:57,545 --> 00:06:59,385
Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.

176
00:06:59,545 --> 00:07:02,285
(They managed to survive the night in the extreme cold.)

177
00:07:03,055 --> 00:07:05,114
(A water splash down the back will be on another level.)

178
00:07:05,115 --> 00:07:06,425
- Okay.
- I'm first.

179
00:07:06,755 --> 00:07:07,755
DinDin.

180
00:07:07,756 --> 00:07:09,495
(The order to hammer the nails)

181
00:07:10,295 --> 00:07:13,025
(Which member will be responsible for the grand finale?)

182
00:07:13,195 --> 00:07:14,825
Hey, this is a big one.

183
00:07:15,465 --> 00:07:17,134
Getting your back splashed with water...

184
00:07:17,135 --> 00:07:18,435
at minus 15°C will be crazy.

185
00:07:18,565 --> 00:07:19,734
(If he can hammer it in one go, he will be exempted.)

186
00:07:19,735 --> 00:07:21,305
You must hit it harder than you think.

187
00:07:21,605 --> 00:07:22,874
(All eyes are...)

188
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:24,104
(on him.)

189
00:07:24,105 --> 00:07:25,705
You must hit it harder than you think.

190
00:07:27,305 --> 00:07:28,305
(Sighing)

191
00:07:28,306 --> 00:07:29,345
Good.

192
00:07:30,275 --> 00:07:33,184
(Unfortunately, DinDin only hammers it in halfway.)

193
00:07:33,185 --> 00:07:34,484
(Relieved)

194
00:07:34,485 --> 00:07:35,684
- That's good.
- Thank you.

195
00:07:35,685 --> 00:07:37,645
- You can succeed on your next turn.
- Thank you.

196
00:07:38,155 --> 00:07:40,084
- Can he put it on the nail?
- It's not easy.

197
00:07:40,085 --> 00:07:41,654
(I'll finish it on my first try.)

198
00:07:41,655 --> 00:07:42,695
It's not easy.

199
00:07:43,955 --> 00:07:45,125
It's not easy.

200
00:07:45,595 --> 00:07:46,894
(Se Yoon also hammers it in halfway.)

201
00:07:46,895 --> 00:07:48,294
- That's good.
- If he can't do it...

202
00:07:48,295 --> 00:07:49,434
- Who's number 3?
- Number 3.

203
00:07:49,435 --> 00:07:50,435
- Number three.
- That's me.

204
00:07:50,436 --> 00:07:51,835
No one missed it so far.

205
00:07:51,995 --> 00:07:53,204
Gosh, this is driving me crazy.

206
00:07:53,205 --> 00:07:54,335
(Heart pounding)

207
00:07:54,705 --> 00:07:55,804
(Seon Ho is the 3rd one to try.)

208
00:07:55,805 --> 00:07:57,235
My gosh, miss it.

209
00:07:58,275 --> 00:07:59,275
(Going in)

210
00:07:59,276 --> 00:08:00,804
- See? I told you it wasn't easy.
- How come everyone is so good?

211
00:08:00,805 --> 00:08:01,874
- Since it's an individual game, - It's not easy.

212
00:08:01,875 --> 00:08:03,114
- everyone is so careful.
- How come everyone is so good?

213
00:08:03,115 --> 00:08:04,115
Hurry up, Jong Min.

214
00:08:04,116 --> 00:08:05,245
- Stop it.
- Please.

215
00:08:05,615 --> 00:08:06,715
Stop it.

216
00:08:07,185 --> 00:08:08,491
(Jong Min is warming up while banging on it loudly.)

217
00:08:08,515 --> 00:08:10,084
(I'll hammer it with the same tempo and strength.)

218
00:08:10,085 --> 00:08:11,085
You're scaring me.

219
00:08:11,086 --> 00:08:12,286
- Darn it.
- His turn is over.

220
00:08:12,655 --> 00:08:14,735
(He fails to hit the nail after wasting his energy.)

221
00:08:15,025 --> 00:08:16,694
- His turn is over.
- I haven't done it yet. What?

222
00:08:16,695 --> 00:08:17,824
- What?
- Come on. Don't lie.

223
00:08:17,825 --> 00:08:18,825
Step back.

224
00:08:18,826 --> 00:08:20,094
- What?
- I can decide when to go.

225
00:08:20,095 --> 00:08:21,865
- Just give it up.
- You already went.

226
00:08:22,635 --> 00:08:23,994
Even if you miss it, your turn is over.

227
00:08:23,995 --> 00:08:25,075
(He misses on his 1st try.)

228
00:08:25,295 --> 00:08:26,434
(Joon is the 5th one to try.)

229
00:08:26,435 --> 00:08:27,835
- Joon.
- Didn't he do it just now?

230
00:08:27,965 --> 00:08:29,204
- Joon.
- Didn't he do it just now?

231
00:08:29,205 --> 00:08:30,605
(He hammers it in a third way in.)

232
00:08:31,135 --> 00:08:33,004
- Gosh, everyone is so good.
- What? Gosh.

233
00:08:33,005 --> 00:08:34,175
(Their 1st try is over.)

234
00:08:34,305 --> 00:08:36,274
(Except for Jong Min, everyone is neck and neck.)

235
00:08:36,275 --> 00:08:37,345
Let's go.

236
00:08:38,075 --> 00:08:39,174
(DinDin's 2nd try)

237
00:08:39,175 --> 00:08:40,885
DinDin.

238
00:08:41,445 --> 00:08:42,515
My gosh.

239
00:08:42,655 --> 00:08:44,154
DinDin, you succeeded.

240
00:08:44,155 --> 00:08:45,155
Okay.

241
00:08:45,715 --> 00:08:47,435
- This is driving me crazy.
- Good for you.

242
00:08:47,585 --> 00:08:48,924
Will doing this leave a stronger impression...

243
00:08:48,925 --> 00:08:50,324
than cleaning up and having breakfast?

244
00:08:50,325 --> 00:08:51,654
- Of course.
- I see.

245
00:08:51,655 --> 00:08:53,294
- Really?
- That's the best way to wrap up.

246
00:08:53,295 --> 00:08:55,595
- Isn't this the best plan?
- It's the best.

247
00:08:56,335 --> 00:08:57,695
He's something else.

248
00:08:58,535 --> 00:09:00,135
(Se Yoon's 2nd try)

249
00:09:00,635 --> 00:09:02,204
- I'm nervous.
- I hope he misses.

250
00:09:02,205 --> 00:09:04,075
- Se Yoon, don't do well.
- Se Yoon.

251
00:09:04,635 --> 00:09:05,775
Don't do well.

252
00:09:06,175 --> 00:09:08,305
- Please.
- You need to do it one more time.

253
00:09:09,005 --> 00:09:10,975
(He failed to hammer it in all the way.)

254
00:09:11,375 --> 00:09:12,884
- Here I go.
- Go.

255
00:09:12,885 --> 00:09:14,645
- Do it just like yesterday. Yes!
- My gosh.

256
00:09:15,245 --> 00:09:16,315
(He missed!)

257
00:09:16,555 --> 00:09:18,154
(Cheering)

258
00:09:18,155 --> 00:09:19,214
Seon Ho.

259
00:09:19,215 --> 00:09:20,854
(Seon Ho misses the nail. Can Jong Min catch up?)

260
00:09:20,855 --> 00:09:22,295
- It's your turn, Jong Min.
- It is?

261
00:09:22,625 --> 00:09:24,195
(Jong Min's 2nd try)

262
00:09:25,095 --> 00:09:26,665
(The nail bends instead of going in.)

263
00:09:27,495 --> 00:09:28,495
Joon!

264
00:09:28,496 --> 00:09:29,634
- Okay.
- What a relief.

265
00:09:29,635 --> 00:09:30,895
I feel bad for these guys.

266
00:09:31,395 --> 00:09:32,835
I want to do it safely.

267
00:09:34,805 --> 00:09:36,105
- All done.
- What do you think?

268
00:09:36,475 --> 00:09:37,604
- What's the best way...
- I did it.

269
00:09:37,605 --> 00:09:38,734
To wrap up the Real Winter Training Center?

270
00:09:38,735 --> 00:09:40,095
A cold-water splash down the back.

271
00:09:40,945 --> 00:09:42,845
- Se Yoon, you succeeded.
- Of course.

272
00:09:43,315 --> 00:09:45,151
We must leave a strong impression on the viewers.

273
00:09:45,175 --> 00:09:47,014
After the trouble we went through, we must finish with a bang.

274
00:09:47,015 --> 00:09:48,144
- Hey.
- I wonder...

275
00:09:48,145 --> 00:09:49,584
if Jong Min can turn the tables around.

276
00:09:49,585 --> 00:09:50,654
(Only 3 members remain now.)

277
00:09:50,655 --> 00:09:52,355
- Seon Ho.
- Anything could happen.

278
00:09:52,615 --> 00:09:53,655
(Hammering)

279
00:09:54,785 --> 00:09:56,194
Seon Ho, you succeeded.

280
00:09:56,195 --> 00:09:57,195
Darn it!

281
00:09:58,155 --> 00:10:00,465
- What's winter for?
- A cold-water splash is the best!

282
00:10:01,495 --> 00:10:02,734
(Laughing)

283
00:10:02,735 --> 00:10:04,495
Seriously. It's fine as long as it's not me.

284
00:10:04,735 --> 00:10:05,764
Jong Min.

285
00:10:05,765 --> 00:10:08,085
If you fail to do it now, it's over. He'll hammer it hard.

286
00:10:08,135 --> 00:10:09,204
Here I go.

287
00:10:09,205 --> 00:10:10,934
Jong Min, you need to go all out.

288
00:10:10,935 --> 00:10:12,335
- Gosh, that's hard.
- Hit it hard.

289
00:10:12,775 --> 00:10:14,805
(This might as well be Jong Min's last try.)

290
00:10:15,305 --> 00:10:17,875
(What will happen to Jong Min?)

291
00:10:18,275 --> 00:10:19,885
(No!)

292
00:10:20,185 --> 00:10:21,214
You should...

293
00:10:21,215 --> 00:10:22,215
(Sighing)

294
00:10:22,645 --> 00:10:24,415
(It still hasn't gone in all the way.)

295
00:10:25,085 --> 00:10:26,555
You should've finished it this time.

296
00:10:26,855 --> 00:10:28,255
(I'm getting the chills.)

297
00:10:28,885 --> 00:10:30,394
(The cold water is dripping down my back.)

298
00:10:30,395 --> 00:10:32,225
- Help him take off his clothes.
- Jong Min.

299
00:10:34,865 --> 00:10:35,964
(Joon will decide who will face the cold-water splash.)

300
00:10:35,965 --> 00:10:37,234
Anything could happen with Joon.

301
00:10:37,235 --> 00:10:39,665
Joon, please miss it. Just hit the board, not the nail.

302
00:10:40,805 --> 00:10:42,105
Joon, I won't look.

303
00:10:42,465 --> 00:10:44,235
(Utterly focused)

304
00:10:45,435 --> 00:10:46,475
Did he do it?

305
00:10:47,045 --> 00:10:48,105
Did he do it?

306
00:10:48,205 --> 00:10:49,575
(I did it!)

307
00:10:49,915 --> 00:10:51,774
- No!
- No, it went all the way in.

308
00:10:51,775 --> 00:10:52,785
That's good.

309
00:10:53,015 --> 00:10:54,614
- I did it.
- No, you jerks.

310
00:10:54,615 --> 00:10:55,815
(Tell me that's not true.)

311
00:10:57,385 --> 00:10:59,824
(Joon's nail is hammered in all the way.)

312
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:00,924
- All right. Joon.
- Let's start.

313
00:11:00,925 --> 00:11:02,254
- I'm sorry.
- You succeeded.

314
00:11:02,255 --> 00:11:04,255
(Joon is the last one to be exempted.)

315
00:11:05,225 --> 00:11:06,424
It will be Jong Min.

316
00:11:06,425 --> 00:11:07,524
(Jong Min will face the water splash down his back.)

317
00:11:07,525 --> 00:11:08,795
I was too greedy at first.

318
00:11:10,495 --> 00:11:11,495
Jong Min.

319
00:11:11,665 --> 00:11:13,145
- Yes.
- We'll remove the microphone.

320
00:11:13,865 --> 00:11:15,034
(Having a lot on his mind)

321
00:11:15,035 --> 00:11:16,704
Getting splashed is one thing.

322
00:11:16,705 --> 00:11:18,674
Taking off clothes in this weather is just torture.

323
00:11:18,675 --> 00:11:19,875
- This is...
- Right.

324
00:11:20,345 --> 00:11:21,675
(Removing his microphone)

325
00:11:22,175 --> 00:11:23,214
Go ahead.

326
00:11:23,215 --> 00:11:24,855
You want us to pour it over your clothes?

327
00:11:25,375 --> 00:11:27,215
Why don't we throw some fire at your back?

328
00:11:27,985 --> 00:11:29,545
Will you bring in the water right away?

329
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:31,714
- It must be here when he's ready.
- Bring in the water.

330
00:11:31,715 --> 00:11:33,385
- Okay.
- Oh, my.

331
00:11:33,885 --> 00:11:35,205
The temperature is at minus 15°C.

332
00:11:36,925 --> 00:11:39,724
(Each time he takes off a layer of his clothes, )

333
00:11:39,725 --> 00:11:41,124
(the cold air penetrates into his skin.)

334
00:11:41,125 --> 00:11:42,564
- It's super cold.
- That's the last one?

335
00:11:42,565 --> 00:11:43,685
- Yes, it is.
- Let's hurry.

336
00:11:43,835 --> 00:11:45,364
- Let's finish it.
- Gosh, it's no joke.

337
00:11:45,365 --> 00:11:46,964
- Jong Min.
- Let's do it right away.

338
00:11:46,965 --> 00:11:48,164
(The cold-water splash down the back at minus 15°C)

339
00:11:48,165 --> 00:11:50,304
- I'll do it without hesitation.
- We'll pour it when you get down.

340
00:11:50,305 --> 00:11:51,334
- Okay.
- Okay.

341
00:11:51,335 --> 00:11:52,774
Jong Min, get it over with. It's too cold for you.

342
00:11:52,775 --> 00:11:53,904
- It's better to get it over with.
- Okay.

343
00:11:53,905 --> 00:11:55,585
The moment you take it off and get down...

344
00:11:55,945 --> 00:11:57,174
The moment you take it off and get down...

345
00:11:57,175 --> 00:11:58,414
(Just watching him go shirtless gives them the chills.)

346
00:11:58,415 --> 00:11:59,984
- I'm getting the chills.
- I'm getting the chills.

347
00:11:59,985 --> 00:12:01,185
- Give me your shirt.
- Hurry.

348
00:12:01,545 --> 00:12:02,545
Give me your shirt.

349
00:12:02,546 --> 00:12:04,031
- Here it goes.
- Bring your bottom up.

350
00:12:04,055 --> 00:12:05,084
- Here it goes.
- Go.

351
00:12:05,085 --> 00:12:06,524
- Here it goes.
- Let's just do it now.

352
00:12:06,525 --> 00:12:07,725
- Be careful!
- Come on.

353
00:12:08,225 --> 00:12:09,225
Jong Min!

354
00:12:09,355 --> 00:12:10,654
- Be careful!
- Gosh.

355
00:12:10,655 --> 00:12:11,725
Jong Min, here it goes.

356
00:12:12,295 --> 00:12:13,295
What's this?

357
00:12:13,296 --> 00:12:14,424
(Terrified)

358
00:12:14,425 --> 00:12:16,964
- I'm sorry, Jong Min.
- Gosh.

359
00:12:16,965 --> 00:12:19,235
(The 1st cold-water splash down the back in 2026)

360
00:12:19,565 --> 00:12:20,565
(Groaning)

361
00:12:26,035 --> 00:12:27,205
- Go!
- Gosh.

362
00:12:27,805 --> 00:12:29,775
(That must feel so cool.)

363
00:12:29,975 --> 00:12:31,044
- Go!
- Gosh.

364
00:12:31,045 --> 00:12:32,775
(I'm sorry, Jong Min.)

365
00:12:33,045 --> 00:12:34,085
Jong Min.

366
00:12:34,445 --> 00:12:40,784
(The cold waterfalls drip down his body.)

367
00:12:40,785 --> 00:12:43,395
Jong Min, my hands are freezing too!

368
00:12:44,095 --> 00:12:45,155
Hurry.

369
00:12:45,355 --> 00:12:46,865
(You're splashing me again?)

370
00:12:48,625 --> 00:12:50,135
Stop it.

371
00:12:52,395 --> 00:12:54,834
(Pouring out all of the water from the bucket)

372
00:12:54,835 --> 00:12:56,675
Give me a towel.

373
00:12:56,935 --> 00:12:58,535
Jong Min, here's your towel.

374
00:12:59,205 --> 00:13:00,445
Here's your towel.

375
00:13:00,975 --> 00:13:02,574
(He can't get a grip...)

376
00:13:02,575 --> 00:13:06,485
(after a cold-water splash at minus 17°C.)

377
00:13:07,415 --> 00:13:09,554
- Here's your towel.
- Watch your back.

378
00:13:09,555 --> 00:13:10,654
- Here.
- Be careful.

379
00:13:10,655 --> 00:13:12,925
- Take care of him.
- Oh, my.

380
00:13:13,625 --> 00:13:14,684
Jong Min, here.

381
00:13:14,685 --> 00:13:16,765
(The younger ones take care of the freezing member.)

382
00:13:17,655 --> 00:13:19,025
I gave him the towel he asked for.

383
00:13:19,825 --> 00:13:21,725
- Great job.
- Gosh.

384
00:13:22,825 --> 00:13:25,185
- Put it over your shoulders.
- Put it over your shoulders.

385
00:13:25,735 --> 00:13:27,215
- Hold on.
- Which shirt do you want?

386
00:13:27,505 --> 00:13:28,804
- What?
- Which shirt do you want?

387
00:13:28,805 --> 00:13:30,735
Your head is steaming. What's going on?

388
00:13:31,175 --> 00:13:33,105
- What's going on?
- Gosh, he's a deity.

389
00:13:33,645 --> 00:13:35,374
- My gosh.
- You worked out a lot, Jong Min.

390
00:13:35,375 --> 00:13:36,815
He looks like a martial artist.

391
00:13:37,145 --> 00:13:38,215
(Laughing)

392
00:13:38,645 --> 00:13:39,885
Look at his pose.

393
00:13:40,915 --> 00:13:43,014
Doesn't he look like Doctor Strange?

394
00:13:43,015 --> 00:13:45,414
He's Master 2 Days 1 Night.

395
00:13:45,415 --> 00:13:46,895
- Keep your head up slightly.
- Gosh.

396
00:13:47,855 --> 00:13:48,885
Seriously, Jong Min.

397
00:13:49,285 --> 00:13:51,325
- What?
- You can overcome the cold.

398
00:13:51,955 --> 00:13:53,064
What is this?

399
00:13:53,065 --> 00:13:54,264
(With the cold-water splash, )

400
00:13:54,265 --> 00:13:56,265
(the Real Winter Training Center of 2026 is over.)

401
00:13:56,395 --> 00:13:57,564
Viewers,

402
00:13:57,565 --> 00:14:00,135
I hope you overcome the cold wave this winter...

403
00:14:00,235 --> 00:14:02,735
and have a great year. We'll be rooting for you!

404
00:14:04,035 --> 00:14:05,535
Korea's best...

405
00:14:05,635 --> 00:14:07,675
Real wild road variety show.

406
00:14:07,775 --> 00:14:08,904
Who are we?

407
00:14:08,905 --> 00:14:10,144
2 Days...

408
00:14:10,145 --> 00:14:13,214
- 1 Night!
- 1 Night!

409
00:14:13,215 --> 00:14:14,215
My gosh!

410
00:14:14,216 --> 00:14:15,284
(Great job, Jong Min.)

411
00:14:15,285 --> 00:14:16,685
- Gosh, you must be cold.
- Oh, my.

412
00:14:16,855 --> 00:14:17,985
Let me get your clothes.

413
00:14:18,385 --> 00:14:19,945
- Oh, no.
- Let's get him some clothes.

414
00:14:20,655 --> 00:14:23,795
(2 Days 1 Night)

415
00:14:24,725 --> 00:14:27,525
(The soft glow of the sun on the west coast...)

416
00:14:28,025 --> 00:14:31,365
(and the orange-hued ocean welcome travelers to this destination.)

417
00:14:32,895 --> 00:14:34,534
(Jeonbuk State)

418
00:14:34,535 --> 00:14:36,875
(Gunsan)

419
00:14:37,435 --> 00:14:40,104
(It's a destination, full of romantic sceneries.)

420
00:14:40,105 --> 00:14:42,675
(Well, it's supposed to be.)

421
00:14:43,045 --> 00:14:45,874
(It's quite foggy in the morning.)

422
00:14:45,875 --> 00:14:47,545
- It feels like I'm dreaming.
- Right.

423
00:14:47,685 --> 00:14:48,845
I can't see ahead.

424
00:14:48,945 --> 00:14:50,154
Gosh, this is pretty bad.

425
00:14:50,155 --> 00:14:52,914
- This is how our future looks.
- What are you talking about?

426
00:14:52,915 --> 00:14:55,124
- I can't see anything ahead.
- You're already jinxing us.

427
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:57,224
- It's dark.
- I can't see anything.

428
00:14:57,225 --> 00:14:58,294
- What a useless thing to say...
- I can't see anything.

429
00:14:58,295 --> 00:14:59,354
In the new year.

430
00:14:59,355 --> 00:15:00,394
- Seriously.
- Hello.

431
00:15:00,395 --> 00:15:02,065
Hello.

432
00:15:02,825 --> 00:15:03,834
(Cheering)

433
00:15:03,835 --> 00:15:04,835
- Hello.
- Yes!

434
00:15:06,035 --> 00:15:07,105
(Screaming)

435
00:15:09,635 --> 00:15:12,635
(For some reason, they're acting more over-the-top.)

436
00:15:12,805 --> 00:15:15,174
- 2 Days 1 Night!
- Who are we?

437
00:15:15,175 --> 00:15:17,544
- 2 Days 1 Night!
- 2 Days 1 Night!

438
00:15:17,545 --> 00:15:18,545
What do we do now?

439
00:15:19,075 --> 00:15:20,444
(Chaotic)

440
00:15:20,445 --> 00:15:22,145
I'm digging our energy level today.

441
00:15:22,185 --> 00:15:24,354
- We've survived!
- Yes.

442
00:15:24,355 --> 00:15:27,954
Viewers! The lowest temperature was minus 17°C or something.

443
00:15:27,955 --> 00:15:29,154
- It was minus 18°C.
- Minus 18, 19, or 20°C.

444
00:15:29,155 --> 00:15:30,324
- It was minus 18°C.
- Minus 18, 19, or 20°C.

445
00:15:30,325 --> 00:15:31,994
It felt like it was at minus 30 or 40°C.

446
00:15:31,995 --> 00:15:33,394
- We survived the cold!
- Right.

447
00:15:33,395 --> 00:15:35,664
We even survived the green house!

448
00:15:35,665 --> 00:15:38,165
- That's right!
- We've survived!

449
00:15:39,495 --> 00:15:42,635
(At the last shoot, they faced extreme cold at minus 17°C.)

450
00:15:43,105 --> 00:15:45,775
(Everything froze at the worst Real Winter Training Center.)

451
00:15:46,475 --> 00:15:48,105
(To survive, )

452
00:15:48,475 --> 00:15:50,275
(they had to jump...)

453
00:15:50,575 --> 00:15:52,315
(and move supplies.)

454
00:15:52,915 --> 00:15:54,885
(Some even fell down.)

455
00:15:55,345 --> 00:15:58,285
(And the night was especially long.)

456
00:15:59,185 --> 00:16:02,225
(They were even out of it momentarily.)

457
00:16:02,755 --> 00:16:05,795
(But they survived!)

458
00:16:06,225 --> 00:16:07,385
Congratulations on making it.

459
00:16:07,525 --> 00:16:11,735
(I've made it.)

460
00:16:12,135 --> 00:16:13,864
- Survivors are the strong ones.
- Yes.

461
00:16:13,865 --> 00:16:15,764
- And we are survivors!
- Right.

462
00:16:15,765 --> 00:16:18,675
Fortunately, our day has started off at above-zero temperatures.

463
00:16:19,005 --> 00:16:20,965
You have no idea how happy I am for this weather!

464
00:16:21,075 --> 00:16:22,144
We've made it. Who are we?

465
00:16:22,145 --> 00:16:23,214
Who are we?

466
00:16:23,215 --> 00:16:25,915
- 2 Days 1 Night!
- 2 Days 1 Night!

467
00:16:28,215 --> 00:16:30,295
- Our energy level is crazy.
- After the last shoot,

468
00:16:30,555 --> 00:16:32,254
I had to lie down for a week which I hadn't done in a while.

469
00:16:32,255 --> 00:16:33,884
- Seriously. I had to lie down.
- Seriously.

470
00:16:33,885 --> 00:16:35,224
- It was really tough.
- I had to stay down.

471
00:16:35,225 --> 00:16:37,824
The next day after shooting the Winter Training Special,

472
00:16:37,825 --> 00:16:39,524
I went to Taiwan to film a show.

473
00:16:39,525 --> 00:16:41,024
You're busy these days.

474
00:16:41,025 --> 00:16:42,364
- Why do you keep going abroad?
- You went to Taiwan?

475
00:16:42,365 --> 00:16:43,735
I went with Hyun Jin.

476
00:16:44,365 --> 00:16:46,565
- I was with him for a week.
- Gosh.

477
00:16:46,865 --> 00:16:49,105
- How was it?
- He couldn't have looked any worse.

478
00:16:49,835 --> 00:16:52,234
(He had to push through the shoot due to fatigue.)

479
00:16:52,235 --> 00:16:54,075
We could barely move.

480
00:16:54,205 --> 00:16:56,674
The fatigue lasted two weeks.

481
00:16:56,675 --> 00:16:58,215
- Jong Min.
- What?

482
00:16:58,275 --> 00:16:59,915
- Were you all right?
- What?

483
00:17:00,115 --> 00:17:01,844
Were you okay? You were the first one I worried about.

484
00:17:01,845 --> 00:17:02,915
Why?

485
00:17:03,015 --> 00:17:05,484
(Why do you think?)

486
00:17:05,485 --> 00:17:06,631
Jong Min, my hands are freezing too!

487
00:17:06,655 --> 00:17:08,324
(It was minus 17°C.)

488
00:17:08,325 --> 00:17:11,395
(But you had cold water down your back.)

489
00:17:11,855 --> 00:17:13,294
- After the last shoot, - How was it for you?

490
00:17:13,295 --> 00:17:15,015
I hadn't felt that fatigued in a long time.

491
00:17:15,295 --> 00:17:17,094
- In a long time?
- No, it's always been tough.

492
00:17:17,095 --> 00:17:18,364
Jong Min, we struggle every week.

493
00:17:18,365 --> 00:17:19,695
But it's been a while for you?

494
00:17:19,905 --> 00:17:21,225
Jong Min, you'd better work hard!

495
00:17:21,705 --> 00:17:22,765
Right!

496
00:17:23,675 --> 00:17:25,434
(Trying to get their energy up for the nth time)

497
00:17:25,435 --> 00:17:26,844
Has anyone heard...

498
00:17:26,845 --> 00:17:28,674
from Boom or Jae Won?

499
00:17:28,675 --> 00:17:30,274
I met Boom.

500
00:17:30,275 --> 00:17:32,751
He had to leave without staying the night due to a prior engagement.

501
00:17:32,775 --> 00:17:34,945
But he said the shoot was over before he realized it.

502
00:17:36,045 --> 00:17:37,414
He closed his eyes for a moment.

503
00:17:37,415 --> 00:17:38,554
Then the shoot was over.

504
00:17:38,555 --> 00:17:40,354
- After...
- He lost his memory.

505
00:17:40,355 --> 00:17:42,524
- He said he lost about two days.
- Yes.

506
00:17:42,525 --> 00:17:43,525
- How's Jae Won?
- Gosh.

507
00:17:43,526 --> 00:17:45,594
- Who talked to him?
- I did get a text from him.

508
00:17:45,595 --> 00:17:47,195
- I got it too.
- Yes, I got his text.

509
00:17:47,425 --> 00:17:49,194
- So...
- He said he was okay.

510
00:17:49,195 --> 00:17:50,664
- I asked if he was okay.
- He said he'd come back.

511
00:17:50,665 --> 00:17:52,294
- He said we felt like family.
- Really?

512
00:17:52,295 --> 00:17:54,464
- If...
- He stayed with us only for a day.

513
00:17:54,465 --> 00:17:56,334
- Our show was different.
- Right.

514
00:17:56,335 --> 00:17:58,434
- He said we bonded quite a lot.
- Yes.

515
00:17:58,435 --> 00:17:59,874
- That's what he told me.
- Really?

516
00:17:59,875 --> 00:18:01,644
Why are you lacking confidence? Did you hear it from someone?

517
00:18:01,645 --> 00:18:03,104
- No.
- Didn't you talk to him?

518
00:18:03,105 --> 00:18:04,114
That's what he texted me.

519
00:18:04,115 --> 00:18:05,921
Why make it sound like someone else told you that?

520
00:18:05,945 --> 00:18:08,615
I get uneasy when I get text messages.

521
00:18:08,815 --> 00:18:09,984
- Really?
- "Why did he text me?"

522
00:18:09,985 --> 00:18:11,854
I saw that you got a license...

523
00:18:11,855 --> 00:18:13,385
in one of your videos.

524
00:18:13,525 --> 00:18:14,784
- Yes.
- For the large vehicles.

525
00:18:14,785 --> 00:18:15,854
- What license is it?
- It's for large vehicles.

526
00:18:15,855 --> 00:18:17,054
- You got it?
- Yes. For large vehicles.

527
00:18:17,055 --> 00:18:18,524
(Driving with one had)

528
00:18:18,525 --> 00:18:19,525
(100 points!)

529
00:18:19,526 --> 00:18:21,524
(He gets the license for large vehicles...)

530
00:18:21,525 --> 00:18:23,795
(with a perfect score.)

531
00:18:24,065 --> 00:18:25,294
- Why did you get the license?
- For the large vehicles.

532
00:18:25,295 --> 00:18:26,534
Will you drive the bus when we travel now?

533
00:18:26,535 --> 00:18:27,734
- That's great.
- Here's what's funny.

534
00:18:27,735 --> 00:18:28,964
It was for a different show.

535
00:18:28,965 --> 00:18:31,211
But so many people mentioned 2 Days 1 Night in the comments.

536
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:33,075
"He can drive the bus on 2 Days 1 Night now."

537
00:18:33,205 --> 00:18:34,574
Why does that matter?

538
00:18:34,575 --> 00:18:35,644
- It was for another show.
- Starting today,

539
00:18:35,645 --> 00:18:36,744
instead of the driver,

540
00:18:36,745 --> 00:18:37,844
- Joon can drive the bus.
- Right.

541
00:18:37,845 --> 00:18:38,915
- Yes.
- For no reason?

542
00:18:39,045 --> 00:18:40,344
- Yes. Drive the bus.
- For no reason?

543
00:18:40,345 --> 00:18:42,015
- They...
- It's not even a mission.

544
00:18:42,215 --> 00:18:44,454
- They'll pay you more.
- They can save on their budget.

545
00:18:44,455 --> 00:18:46,154
- Show us how you drive a bus.
- Yes.

546
00:18:46,155 --> 00:18:48,054
So I sit and drive like this.

547
00:18:48,055 --> 00:18:49,055
(This is how it goes.)

548
00:18:49,725 --> 00:18:51,525
(He's very happy to have gotten the license.)

549
00:18:51,655 --> 00:18:53,154
(Looking forward to the day when Joon drives for us)

550
00:18:53,155 --> 00:18:54,195
Great.

551
00:18:54,395 --> 00:18:56,025
But it's so foggy today.

552
00:18:56,325 --> 00:18:58,534
- On my way here, - Yes.

553
00:18:58,535 --> 00:19:00,604
I fell asleep in the car. Then I woke up.

554
00:19:00,605 --> 00:19:03,134
- Yes. Seriously.
- I couldn't see anything.

555
00:19:03,135 --> 00:19:05,074
- I thought I was dead.
- Seriously.

556
00:19:05,075 --> 00:19:08,174
"I must be in a different realm."

557
00:19:08,175 --> 00:19:09,444
- Yes.
- Right.

558
00:19:09,445 --> 00:19:12,915
It got foggy for the first time here today.

559
00:19:13,115 --> 00:19:14,115
- Really?
- What?

560
00:19:14,116 --> 00:19:15,414
- It's their 1st foggy day.
- It's their 1st foggy day?

561
00:19:15,415 --> 00:19:16,554
- Right?
- That makes no sense.

562
00:19:16,555 --> 00:19:17,914
- Gunsan...
- Foggy days are rare here.

563
00:19:17,915 --> 00:19:18,954
- Foggy days?
- Yes.

564
00:19:18,955 --> 00:19:20,354
- It's rarely foggy here.
- Usually,

565
00:19:20,355 --> 00:19:22,254
we can see the ocean from here.

566
00:19:22,255 --> 00:19:23,255
The view from here is beautiful.

567
00:19:23,255 --> 00:19:24,255
- Really?
- We can't see anything.

568
00:19:24,256 --> 00:19:25,854
- I can't see a thing.
- This rarely happens.

569
00:19:25,855 --> 00:19:27,794
- Today is one of those rare days.
- I just realized it was an ocean.

570
00:19:27,795 --> 00:19:29,235
- I can't see anything.
- Usually...

571
00:19:29,395 --> 00:19:31,834
As for our destination for today's trip in Gunsan...

572
00:19:31,835 --> 00:19:32,875
(It's 1 hour away by car.)

573
00:19:33,265 --> 00:19:36,935
sixty-three large and small islands stretch out like a panorama.

574
00:19:37,135 --> 00:19:39,034
It's the representative archipelago on the west coast.

575
00:19:39,035 --> 00:19:40,844
We'll be traveling Gogunsan Islands...

576
00:19:40,845 --> 00:19:42,375
- today.
- Gogunsan Islands.

577
00:19:43,105 --> 00:19:48,284
(Each island has its own charm.)

578
00:19:48,285 --> 00:19:49,545
The main islands...

579
00:19:50,185 --> 00:19:52,514
- are connected by bridges.
- Yes, apparently.

580
00:19:52,515 --> 00:19:54,624
This destination is beloved for its islands,

581
00:19:54,625 --> 00:19:56,055
perfect for romantic drives.

582
00:19:56,255 --> 00:19:58,294
Magnificent views of nature will be the focus of our trip.

583
00:19:58,295 --> 00:20:00,665
- The theme of today's concept is...
- What is it? Please.

584
00:20:00,995 --> 00:20:02,994
Gogunsan Islands Race.

585
00:20:02,995 --> 00:20:04,334
- Race?
- Race?

586
00:20:04,335 --> 00:20:05,364
- Yes.
- Gosh.

587
00:20:05,365 --> 00:20:06,735
- It's a team mission.
- Okay.

588
00:20:07,265 --> 00:20:10,935
After completing all the missions at each spot,

589
00:20:11,235 --> 00:20:14,575
all of you must arrive at the final spot by 1pm.

590
00:20:14,805 --> 00:20:17,244
Then as a reward, you will get a camping meal...

591
00:20:17,245 --> 00:20:19,074
with seafood from the west coast for lunch.

592
00:20:19,075 --> 00:20:21,544
If it's a camping meal, there should be a barbecue grill.

593
00:20:21,545 --> 00:20:23,185
- There should be seafood too.
- Exactly.

594
00:20:23,245 --> 00:20:25,245
Here are the ingredients we prepared for the meal.

595
00:20:25,755 --> 00:20:26,824
Blue crabs.

596
00:20:26,825 --> 00:20:28,425
(Sweet blue crabs, full of roe)

597
00:20:29,525 --> 00:20:31,524
- A famous local ingredient, plaice.
- Plaice.

598
00:20:31,525 --> 00:20:32,794
- That sounds good.
- Plaice.

599
00:20:32,795 --> 00:20:34,475
(Plaice dried in the sea breeze of Gunsan)

600
00:20:34,925 --> 00:20:36,665
(The best way to enjoy it...)

601
00:20:37,035 --> 00:20:38,935
(is to grill it and tear it.)

602
00:20:39,295 --> 00:20:40,695
There will be murices and scallops.

603
00:20:41,135 --> 00:20:42,581
- That sounds good.
- We can grill them.

604
00:20:42,605 --> 00:20:45,435
(Ramyeon, a must-try dish while camping)

605
00:20:45,805 --> 00:20:47,875
(Kimchi)

606
00:20:48,275 --> 00:20:50,545
(There will be rice too.)

607
00:20:50,915 --> 00:20:53,614
(The camping meal comes with six ingredients.)

608
00:20:53,615 --> 00:20:54,615
However,

609
00:20:54,616 --> 00:20:57,084
if you fail to arrive at the final spot on time,

610
00:20:57,085 --> 00:20:59,784
you will lose 1 dish for every 5 minutes you're late.

611
00:20:59,785 --> 00:21:01,655
Gosh, five minutes are too tight.

612
00:21:01,925 --> 00:21:03,624
That's tight. Only five minutes?

613
00:21:03,625 --> 00:21:05,925
- We'd lose them all in 30 minutes.
- Right.

614
00:21:06,255 --> 00:21:08,094
You said you'd remove 1 dish for every 5 minutes.

615
00:21:08,095 --> 00:21:09,294
Will you start with the main dish?

616
00:21:09,295 --> 00:21:11,064
Or can we decide which one to remove first?

617
00:21:11,065 --> 00:21:12,165
You're so smart.

618
00:21:12,395 --> 00:21:13,804
- I'm 100 percent certain...
- You're smart.

619
00:21:13,805 --> 00:21:15,064
- he'll be mean about it.
- Yes.

620
00:21:15,065 --> 00:21:16,304
- He'll remove seafood first.
- Right.

621
00:21:16,305 --> 00:21:18,185
- You can't start with the mains.
- He's smart.

622
00:21:18,535 --> 00:21:19,634
(At 1pm, they get 6 dishes.)

623
00:21:19,635 --> 00:21:20,644
(At 1:05pm, they get 5 dishes.)

624
00:21:20,645 --> 00:21:21,645
(At 1:10pm, they get 4 dishes.)

625
00:21:21,646 --> 00:21:22,974
(At 1:15pm, they get 3 dishes. At 1:20pm, they get 2 dishes.)

626
00:21:22,975 --> 00:21:24,274
(At 1:25pm, they get 1 dish. At 1:30pm, they get no food.)

627
00:21:24,275 --> 00:21:25,914
(The number of dishes will go down.)

628
00:21:25,915 --> 00:21:28,196
You can only eat the dishes you get from a random draw...

629
00:21:28,445 --> 00:21:31,084
based on the number of dishes you've earned.

630
00:21:31,085 --> 00:21:32,215
I see. Only those dishes.

631
00:21:32,685 --> 00:21:34,285
Then it's fair.

632
00:21:34,425 --> 00:21:35,755
Once you finish the race,

633
00:21:36,085 --> 00:21:38,355
I'll tell you about the random draw.

634
00:21:39,055 --> 00:21:40,494
Whoever messes up today better be ready.

635
00:21:40,495 --> 00:21:41,694
- Okay. No fooling around today.
- Yes.

636
00:21:41,695 --> 00:21:43,194
I'm going to punch them in the belly. I'm serious.

637
00:21:43,195 --> 00:21:44,864
- Seriously. I want to eat them all.
- Okay.

638
00:21:44,865 --> 00:21:47,005
Here's the first mission spot.

639
00:21:47,635 --> 00:21:49,434
It's here. No?

640
00:21:49,435 --> 00:21:50,875
(Nervous)

641
00:21:51,205 --> 00:21:53,375
It's the town shuttle bus right over there.

642
00:21:53,775 --> 00:21:55,504
- The town shuttle bus.
- The yellow one, right?

643
00:21:55,505 --> 00:21:56,545
It will begin now.

644
00:21:56,605 --> 00:21:58,645
Come on. Don't be like that. I'll be out of breath.

645
00:21:59,375 --> 00:22:01,184
- The race...
- You really should work out.

646
00:22:01,185 --> 00:22:02,245
Let's switch places.

647
00:22:02,745 --> 00:22:04,055
- will begin now.
- Okay.

648
00:22:04,315 --> 00:22:05,415
Go.

649
00:22:05,815 --> 00:22:07,154
- Get on it.
- We're on the same team.

650
00:22:07,155 --> 00:22:08,155
Come here.

651
00:22:08,655 --> 00:22:09,685
- Let's go.
- No!

652
00:22:09,825 --> 00:22:11,425
- No.
- We're playing as a team.

653
00:22:11,595 --> 00:22:13,294
- Right. We're playing as a team.
- It's a team mission. Why run?

654
00:22:13,295 --> 00:22:15,825
- Time is gold.
- Let's not run then.

655
00:22:16,425 --> 00:22:17,495
Please!

656
00:22:18,265 --> 00:22:20,404
(They start off their morning with a run.)

657
00:22:20,405 --> 00:22:22,304
- What's wrong with him?
- Time is gold.

658
00:22:22,305 --> 00:22:23,475
- What?
- What's this?

659
00:22:24,105 --> 00:22:25,205
What's this?

660
00:22:26,375 --> 00:22:27,475
What is that?

661
00:22:27,805 --> 00:22:29,405
- Let's get Se Yoon to sit there.
- Yes.

662
00:22:29,705 --> 00:22:31,374
- What's that?
- Is it an electric chair?

663
00:22:31,375 --> 00:22:32,475
What's this?

664
00:22:32,545 --> 00:22:33,914
Se Yoon, you have to sit there.

665
00:22:33,915 --> 00:22:35,391
- Everyone. I'll explain it now.
- What's going on?

666
00:22:35,415 --> 00:22:36,884
(They run to their first mission spot.)

667
00:22:36,885 --> 00:22:38,254
It's the Gogunsan Islands Race.

668
00:22:38,255 --> 00:22:40,254
- Okay.
- Here's your mission.

669
00:22:40,255 --> 00:22:41,285
Let's do this!

670
00:22:41,485 --> 00:22:43,225
It's the Infinite Flour Nightmare.

671
00:22:43,725 --> 00:22:44,725
All right.

672
00:22:44,726 --> 00:22:45,824
(Even the name sounds ominous.)

673
00:22:45,825 --> 00:22:48,324
- I have a bad feeling about this.
- You will have to keep trying...

674
00:22:48,325 --> 00:22:51,094
until you complete three rounds.

675
00:22:51,095 --> 00:22:52,095
Okay.

676
00:22:52,096 --> 00:22:54,605
Four of you will try out for the mission.

677
00:22:54,635 --> 00:22:57,405
One of you will sit under the balloon filled with flour.

678
00:22:57,575 --> 00:22:59,504
Every time the members fail the mission,

679
00:22:59,505 --> 00:23:00,674
he will be splashed with flour.

680
00:23:00,675 --> 00:23:02,605
- Jong Min, you're the eldest. Go.
- I... Yes.

681
00:23:02,975 --> 00:23:05,121
- You're the eldest. So...
- No. Play rock-paper-scissors.

682
00:23:05,145 --> 00:23:06,774
- No, let's not do that.
- Let's play rock-paper-scissors.

683
00:23:06,775 --> 00:23:08,114
- No way. Jong Min.
- Se Yoon.

684
00:23:08,115 --> 00:23:09,644
- You should do it.
- I have something to say about it.

685
00:23:09,645 --> 00:23:11,554
Let's be rational. Those who woke up early and went to the salon...

686
00:23:11,555 --> 00:23:13,654
- should be excluded.
- Right, they should be.

687
00:23:13,655 --> 00:23:15,724
- Seriously. Then why would we...
- We wouldn't go to the salon then.

688
00:23:15,725 --> 00:23:16,784
I'll come to the opening segment...

689
00:23:16,785 --> 00:23:17,894
without a shower, looking like a beggar.

690
00:23:17,895 --> 00:23:19,354
- Why go to the salon?
- Who looks like a beggar?

691
00:23:19,355 --> 00:23:20,795
You told me to go to the salon.

692
00:23:20,965 --> 00:23:22,494
- I didn't go.
- Yes.

693
00:23:22,495 --> 00:23:23,934
Why are you waking us up at dawn?

694
00:23:23,935 --> 00:23:25,734
- You just go and sit there.
- Why me?

695
00:23:25,735 --> 00:23:27,104
- What about you? You didn't go.
- I...

696
00:23:27,105 --> 00:23:28,535
I can do everything by myself.

697
00:23:28,935 --> 00:23:29,935
(Laughing)

698
00:23:29,936 --> 00:23:31,734
- Can you tell us about the mission?
- Yes.

699
00:23:31,735 --> 00:23:33,074
We should pick the members...

700
00:23:33,075 --> 00:23:34,515
- suitable for the mission.
- Right.

701
00:23:34,645 --> 00:23:36,281
- It's not about the salons.
- He's wise.

702
00:23:36,305 --> 00:23:37,314
- You do have a point.
- Right.

703
00:23:37,315 --> 00:23:38,315
- Yes.
- Yes.

704
00:23:38,316 --> 00:23:40,214
- All right. What's the mission?
- The first round is...

705
00:23:40,215 --> 00:23:41,385
- I know.
- What is it?

706
00:23:41,615 --> 00:23:43,684
- It's Relay Cham, Cham, Cham.
- Cham, Cham, Cham?

707
00:23:43,685 --> 00:23:45,954
- Hold on. DinDin, you're playing.
- Yes.

708
00:23:45,955 --> 00:23:46,955
- You're good.
- Okay.

709
00:23:46,956 --> 00:23:48,284
- I'm being fair, right?
- Yes. You are.

710
00:23:48,285 --> 00:23:49,701
- Right? You're playing. Okay.
- You're fair.

711
00:23:49,725 --> 00:23:52,354
To complete the first-round mission, four of you must successfully...

712
00:23:52,355 --> 00:23:53,394
- play defense.
- If we do...

713
00:23:53,395 --> 00:23:55,094
- Okay.
- All of you must succeed.

714
00:23:55,095 --> 00:23:57,794
It won't be easy to win the game four times in a row.

715
00:23:57,795 --> 00:24:00,035
The probability is 12.5 percent. No, it's 12.25 percent.

716
00:24:00,305 --> 00:24:01,604
If you fail, the balloon will pop.

717
00:24:01,605 --> 00:24:02,605
Okay.

718
00:24:02,606 --> 00:24:04,134
What if we succeed? We'll move on?

719
00:24:04,135 --> 00:24:05,781
- We'll go to the next round?
- The next round?

720
00:24:05,805 --> 00:24:06,944
We'll go to the next round?

721
00:24:06,945 --> 00:24:07,974
If we play it ten times,

722
00:24:07,975 --> 00:24:09,495
- we'll complete the mission.
- Right.

723
00:24:09,605 --> 00:24:11,845
The worst player should sit on the chair.

724
00:24:11,945 --> 00:24:12,945
Cham, cham, cham.

725
00:24:12,946 --> 00:24:14,244
- See? You're bad at it.
- No.

726
00:24:14,245 --> 00:24:16,344
(He's the type to create trouble.)

727
00:24:16,345 --> 00:24:17,415
You're bad at it.

728
00:24:17,515 --> 00:24:18,814
- Really?
- Hey. Cham, cham, cham.

729
00:24:18,815 --> 00:24:20,114
(Testing Joon too)

730
00:24:20,115 --> 00:24:23,324
See? Cham, cham, cham.

731
00:24:23,325 --> 00:24:25,554
(Stalling his moves without letting Joon realize it)

732
00:24:25,555 --> 00:24:26,555
You're bad at it!

733
00:24:26,556 --> 00:24:28,565
- It should be Joon.
- Go ahead. Sit.

734
00:24:30,295 --> 00:24:31,334
Speak up if you have something to say.

735
00:24:31,335 --> 00:24:32,335
Cham, cham, cham.

736
00:24:32,336 --> 00:24:34,165
(He's being ridiculed thoroughly.)

737
00:24:34,435 --> 00:24:37,234
(Why do I keep losing?)

738
00:24:37,235 --> 00:24:38,705
How can you never win even once?

739
00:24:38,835 --> 00:24:40,635
- Rock-paper-scissors.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

740
00:24:41,275 --> 00:24:43,675
This cannot be helped.

741
00:24:43,845 --> 00:24:45,475
We will win for you.

742
00:24:45,615 --> 00:24:47,244
Joon, just wait.

743
00:24:47,245 --> 00:24:48,814
He has no skills, and he's not lucky either.

744
00:24:48,815 --> 00:24:49,984
(Fumbling with his clothes)

745
00:24:49,985 --> 00:24:52,261
You have to take off everything when you get flour on it.

746
00:24:52,285 --> 00:24:53,484
- It'll be hard to remove it.
- Do I have to take everything off?

747
00:24:53,485 --> 00:24:54,824
It's hard to remove flour.

748
00:24:54,825 --> 00:24:56,784
(It's hard to remove flour.)

749
00:24:56,785 --> 00:24:58,594
You also have to take off your pants.

750
00:24:58,595 --> 00:24:59,595
(Laughing)

751
00:24:59,825 --> 00:25:00,964
That's true.

752
00:25:00,965 --> 00:25:02,494
- You must take off your sweater.
- You should take off your sweater.

753
00:25:02,495 --> 00:25:03,595
Of course.

754
00:25:04,235 --> 00:25:05,464
Keep your long underwear only.

755
00:25:05,465 --> 00:25:07,165
I should help him with the microphone.

756
00:25:08,765 --> 00:25:10,034
- There you go.
- Is this good?

757
00:25:10,035 --> 00:25:11,704
- Goodness.
- That will work.

758
00:25:11,705 --> 00:25:12,774
(A microphone earring)

759
00:25:12,775 --> 00:25:14,705
That will work. Go and sit down quickly.

760
00:25:14,905 --> 00:25:16,245
Your earring looks nice.

761
00:25:17,975 --> 00:25:18,975
(He's only wearing his long underwear in the freezing cold.)

762
00:25:18,976 --> 00:25:20,285
This is ridiculous.

763
00:25:22,945 --> 00:25:24,414
- He has a nice body.
- He really does.

764
00:25:24,415 --> 00:25:27,185
- What's with his shoulders?
- His shoulders are really built.

765
00:25:27,525 --> 00:25:28,724
- Let's go.
- We're ready.

766
00:25:28,725 --> 00:25:29,725
Let's start right away.

767
00:25:29,726 --> 00:25:31,554
Each of you will come out and play.

768
00:25:31,555 --> 00:25:32,594
- DinDin.
- DinDin, you start.

769
00:25:32,595 --> 00:25:34,071
- You should go first.
- Take control from the start.

770
00:25:34,095 --> 00:25:35,694
- Do we play three times?
- Please.

771
00:25:35,695 --> 00:25:37,895
- Is it 3 consecutive times?
- All 4 of us have to win.

772
00:25:38,135 --> 00:25:39,534
(Cham, Cham, Cham with Director Joo)

773
00:25:39,535 --> 00:25:41,435
(DinDin has an undefeated record.)

774
00:25:41,765 --> 00:25:46,635
(Director Joo's nemesis in the game of Cham, Cham, Cham)

775
00:25:47,175 --> 00:25:49,205
- Which way will you go?
- This way.

776
00:25:49,745 --> 00:25:50,775
Please.

777
00:25:51,815 --> 00:25:52,815
Please.

778
00:25:52,816 --> 00:25:54,044
(He'll be covered with flour if DinDin loses.)

779
00:25:54,045 --> 00:25:55,885
I'll go this way.

780
00:25:56,845 --> 00:25:57,854
(A psychological warfare starts.)

781
00:25:57,855 --> 00:25:59,375
- I'll definitely go this way.
- Okay.

782
00:25:59,585 --> 00:26:01,354
If Director Joo loses,

783
00:26:01,355 --> 00:26:02,624
- it'll be easy for us.
- Right.

784
00:26:02,625 --> 00:26:03,694
- We're bound to win.
- Let's start.

785
00:26:03,695 --> 00:26:04,794
Cham, cham, cham.

786
00:26:04,795 --> 00:26:06,494
(DinDin wins again.)

787
00:26:06,495 --> 00:26:08,024
Director Joo can never win.

788
00:26:08,025 --> 00:26:10,934
(Traumatized)

789
00:26:10,935 --> 00:26:12,835
Shouldn't he play with me once?

790
00:26:13,135 --> 00:26:14,204
Here we go.

791
00:26:14,205 --> 00:26:15,205
(Chanting)

792
00:26:15,305 --> 00:26:18,174
Left.

793
00:26:18,175 --> 00:26:19,805
Right. Left.

794
00:26:20,035 --> 00:26:22,205
Center.

795
00:26:22,745 --> 00:26:25,075
- Let's start.
- What's wrong with your face?

796
00:26:25,315 --> 00:26:26,675
- I have a plan too.
- Okay.

797
00:26:26,915 --> 00:26:27,915
Are you trying to confuse him?

798
00:26:27,916 --> 00:26:28,985
Cham, cham, cham.

799
00:26:29,285 --> 00:26:30,814
- How did you know?
- You failed.

800
00:26:30,815 --> 00:26:31,815
Okay.

801
00:26:33,315 --> 00:26:34,324
- You failed.
- Okay.

802
00:26:34,325 --> 00:26:35,325
(Popping)

803
00:26:36,285 --> 00:26:37,295
(Laughing)

804
00:26:38,825 --> 00:26:41,825
We have a very slim chance of winning in this game.

805
00:26:42,225 --> 00:26:43,934
Joon, it's okay. Brush it off.

806
00:26:43,935 --> 00:26:45,494
- Just brush it off once.
- Brush it off.

807
00:26:45,495 --> 00:26:47,465
Brush it off and stand up.

808
00:26:47,535 --> 00:26:49,264
- Do I go again?
- Of course. Who else would go?

809
00:26:49,265 --> 00:26:50,775
Do I just stay seated?

810
00:26:50,975 --> 00:26:52,504
We have to play this quickly.

811
00:26:52,505 --> 00:26:53,675
- Let's do it fast.
- Okay.

812
00:26:54,575 --> 00:26:55,645
It's cold.

813
00:26:56,075 --> 00:26:57,144
We'll play in this order.

814
00:26:57,145 --> 00:26:58,145
- Okay, here we go.
- Okay.

815
00:26:58,146 --> 00:26:59,321
- Start right after me.
- We can do it.

816
00:26:59,345 --> 00:27:01,044
Don't say which direction you'll go.

817
00:27:01,045 --> 00:27:02,184
- Just do it.
- Let's start right away.

818
00:27:02,185 --> 00:27:03,914
You can do it.

819
00:27:03,915 --> 00:27:04,915
(Se Yoon goes first.)

820
00:27:04,916 --> 00:27:06,285
- What?
- Cham, cham, cham.

821
00:27:06,485 --> 00:27:07,684
- Go.
- Okay.

822
00:27:07,685 --> 00:27:08,685
(Se Yoon made it.)

823
00:27:08,686 --> 00:27:10,525
- Cham, cham, cham.
- He got it.

824
00:27:10,825 --> 00:27:12,095
- We got it.
- Hurry.

825
00:27:12,295 --> 00:27:13,295
Cham, cham, cham.

826
00:27:13,296 --> 00:27:14,564
He got it.

827
00:27:14,565 --> 00:27:15,864
- Cham, cham, cham.
- He got it.

828
00:27:15,865 --> 00:27:16,865
We got it.

829
00:27:16,866 --> 00:27:18,194
- It's DinDin's turn.
- We got it.

830
00:27:18,195 --> 00:27:19,764
Hey, Lim Cheol.

831
00:27:19,765 --> 00:27:20,805
Lim Cheol.

832
00:27:21,305 --> 00:27:23,605
It's DinDin's turn. He'll make it.

833
00:27:24,035 --> 00:27:25,735
Which way will you go?

834
00:27:26,075 --> 00:27:27,504
- Which way?
- I won't say it.

835
00:27:27,505 --> 00:27:28,604
Which way will you go?

836
00:27:28,605 --> 00:27:30,374
- You can do it.
- Don't give him any look.

837
00:27:30,375 --> 00:27:32,144
- You have a 50-percent chance.
- I'll turn right.

838
00:27:32,145 --> 00:27:33,714
- Okay.
- Here it is.

839
00:27:33,715 --> 00:27:34,985
- I'll turn right.
- Okay.

840
00:27:35,415 --> 00:27:36,514
Look at me in the eye.

841
00:27:36,515 --> 00:27:37,815
- I'll turn right.
- Okay.

842
00:27:38,185 --> 00:27:40,484
- Come on.
- Director Joo already lost.

843
00:27:40,485 --> 00:27:41,685
His hands are trembling.

844
00:27:41,925 --> 00:27:44,694
It's here.

845
00:27:44,695 --> 00:27:46,255
(He can't delay it any longer.)

846
00:27:47,025 --> 00:27:48,025
Cham, cham...

847
00:27:48,026 --> 00:27:49,925
(He shouted.)

848
00:27:49,988 --> 00:27:50,613
Cham, cham, cham.

849
00:27:50,801 --> 00:27:54,170
(DinDin won again.)

850
00:27:54,171 --> 00:27:55,811
Okay!

851
00:27:56,911 --> 00:28:00,210
(They barely completed Round 1 on their 2nd try.)

852
00:28:00,211 --> 00:28:01,951
Look how disappointed he is.

853
00:28:02,151 --> 00:28:04,921
(He failed to get over DinDin's wall again this time.)

854
00:28:05,751 --> 00:28:07,821
(Tapping)

855
00:28:08,451 --> 00:28:10,420
- That was great.
- Let's keep it up.

856
00:28:10,421 --> 00:28:13,191
Let's move onto the second round.

857
00:28:14,131 --> 00:28:16,491
- Am I done with the flour?
- That's right.

858
00:28:16,801 --> 00:28:18,200
The person for the flour penalty must be replaced.

859
00:28:18,201 --> 00:28:19,501
- Okay.
- He has to be replaced.

860
00:28:19,861 --> 00:28:21,401
What kind of rule is that?

861
00:28:22,701 --> 00:28:23,840
That's ridiculous.

862
00:28:23,841 --> 00:28:25,040
His reaction...

863
00:28:25,041 --> 00:28:26,271
Mission Round Two.

864
00:28:26,441 --> 00:28:28,340
It's Table Tennis on a Dining Table Relay.

865
00:28:28,341 --> 00:28:29,370
Did you hear that?

866
00:28:29,371 --> 00:28:30,440
- I'm good at table tennis.
- Me too.

867
00:28:30,441 --> 00:28:32,110
- I'm also good at it.
- You're good at it.

868
00:28:32,111 --> 00:28:34,381
Each of the four members will get a turn in a relay.

869
00:28:34,711 --> 00:28:36,820
It's successful only when you knock down both balls.

870
00:28:36,821 --> 00:28:37,821
- Can it break?
- Hey.

871
00:28:37,822 --> 00:28:40,050
- Knock down 2 balls?
- We can't knock down even 1.

872
00:28:40,051 --> 00:28:42,490
Pick one person to sit underneath the flour balloon.

873
00:28:42,491 --> 00:28:43,790
- Let's do this.
- The number of times?

874
00:28:43,791 --> 00:28:45,890
- The one who fails the earliest.
- I can do this all day long.

875
00:28:45,891 --> 00:28:46,960
Let's keep going.

876
00:28:46,961 --> 00:28:48,667
- Start bouncing it simultaneously.
- Okay.

877
00:28:48,691 --> 00:28:50,300
- Ready, set...
- I haven't practiced it yet.

878
00:28:50,301 --> 00:28:51,331
- Go.
- Go.

879
00:28:54,271 --> 00:28:55,951
The one who drops it will go and sit down.

880
00:28:56,601 --> 00:29:00,341
(They're very serious over something so minor.)

881
00:29:01,271 --> 00:29:03,511
(While the clear sounds resonate everywhere)

882
00:29:04,581 --> 00:29:06,141
(Oh, no!)

883
00:29:06,711 --> 00:29:08,150
(Jong Min's table tennis ball bounces off and falls.)

884
00:29:08,151 --> 00:29:10,051
- Who is it?
- It's Jong Min.

885
00:29:10,221 --> 00:29:11,680
- Okay.
- Jong Min, go and sit down.

886
00:29:11,681 --> 00:29:12,880
- Go quickly.
- Hurry up.

887
00:29:12,881 --> 00:29:13,891
Go quickly.

888
00:29:15,321 --> 00:29:16,321
Goodness.

889
00:29:16,621 --> 00:29:18,660
(A marksman who never misses)

890
00:29:18,661 --> 00:29:19,921
Why did you mess with me?

891
00:29:20,161 --> 00:29:21,461
- I mean...
- Goodness.

892
00:29:22,361 --> 00:29:24,100
- Let's do it immediately.
- Shout "start" before starting.

893
00:29:24,101 --> 00:29:26,201
We'll start. You can relax.

894
00:29:26,661 --> 00:29:28,231
Jong Min, we'll make it.

895
00:29:28,531 --> 00:29:30,201
- We'll start.
- Is it good?

896
00:29:31,871 --> 00:29:33,141
(DinDin failed.)

897
00:29:33,201 --> 00:29:34,411
What are you doing?

898
00:29:34,741 --> 00:29:35,741
Joon.

899
00:29:35,742 --> 00:29:37,941
- Do your best.
- Joon, you have to make it.

900
00:29:39,341 --> 00:29:40,350
He got it.

901
00:29:40,351 --> 00:29:41,881
(Joon failed.)

902
00:29:42,081 --> 00:29:44,151
(Third Player Seon Ho must succeed no matter what.)

903
00:29:45,421 --> 00:29:47,251
(The direction was accurate.)

904
00:29:48,991 --> 00:29:50,891
(But he didn't make it.)

905
00:29:52,661 --> 00:29:54,761
(Doomed)

906
00:29:54,991 --> 00:29:57,431
- Didn't we fail already?
- He could knock down both of them.

907
00:29:57,631 --> 00:30:00,401
(Is it time for me to step up?)

908
00:30:00,531 --> 00:30:03,171
(Fiercely measuring the angle to take down both targets in one go)

909
00:30:03,441 --> 00:30:05,571
(Please, Se Yoon)

910
00:30:10,781 --> 00:30:11,811
Yes.

911
00:30:15,411 --> 00:30:17,521
(Throwing the plate)

912
00:30:17,981 --> 00:30:20,491
(He knocked down both of them by cheating.)

913
00:30:21,321 --> 00:30:23,351
(I knew that this would happen.)

914
00:30:23,591 --> 00:30:25,120
(A refreshing shower with flour)

915
00:30:25,121 --> 00:30:26,221
I feel bad for him.

916
00:30:26,321 --> 00:30:28,490
The side of him that we saw during Real Winter is coming back.

917
00:30:28,491 --> 00:30:29,630
- Shake it off.
- Here it comes.

918
00:30:29,631 --> 00:30:32,261
There he is.

919
00:30:32,401 --> 00:30:34,601
Get up. Goodness.

920
00:30:35,501 --> 00:30:38,470
(The back washing deity is followed by the flour deity.)

921
00:30:38,471 --> 00:30:40,811
- This is difficult.
- It's impossible.

922
00:30:41,171 --> 00:30:42,570
- That was nice, Jong Min.
- I'll start.

923
00:30:42,571 --> 00:30:43,691
(Don't you dare fail again.)

924
00:30:43,881 --> 00:30:45,411
- I'll start.
- Are we starting?

925
00:30:45,881 --> 00:30:46,981
Are we starting?

926
00:30:47,981 --> 00:30:49,251
(DinDin failed.)

927
00:30:49,451 --> 00:30:50,751
Let's go, Joon.

928
00:30:52,621 --> 00:30:53,991
(His ball is not even close.)

929
00:30:54,221 --> 00:30:56,691
(It's Se Yoon's turn already without hope.)

930
00:30:58,191 --> 00:30:59,721
- Gosh.
- Oh, my.

931
00:31:01,731 --> 00:31:04,961
(Se Yoon succeeded neatly.)

932
00:31:06,161 --> 00:31:08,300
(The hope comes back.)

933
00:31:08,301 --> 00:31:10,101
- Seon Ho just has to hit one.
- Start.

934
00:31:10,171 --> 00:31:11,500
- Seon Ho.
- Hey, Seon Ho.

935
00:31:11,501 --> 00:31:13,240
If you miss, you'll replace Jong Min.

936
00:31:13,241 --> 00:31:14,740
(If you miss, you'll get the flour.)

937
00:31:14,741 --> 00:31:15,741
- Gosh.
- You'll replace him.

938
00:31:15,742 --> 00:31:17,741
If you fail, you'll replace Jong Min.

939
00:31:17,911 --> 00:31:19,440
Concentrate.

940
00:31:19,441 --> 00:31:20,481
You'll replace him.

941
00:31:20,811 --> 00:31:23,211
(He hit it.)

942
00:31:26,991 --> 00:31:28,351
- Replace him.
- You failed.

943
00:31:28,591 --> 00:31:30,420
(The last ball missed it slightly.)

944
00:31:30,421 --> 00:31:31,421
(Popping)

945
00:31:32,391 --> 00:31:33,690
(Moaning)

946
00:31:33,691 --> 00:31:34,930
Jong Min is transforming again.

947
00:31:34,931 --> 00:31:36,161
(2 consecutive flour bombs)

948
00:31:37,301 --> 00:31:40,061
(No matter how much he shakes it off, the flour is endless.)

949
00:31:40,301 --> 00:31:42,731
Jong Min, let me try it with the other side.

950
00:31:43,301 --> 00:31:44,540
- No, you sit down.
- Why not?

951
00:31:44,541 --> 00:31:45,570
- It's you.
- No.

952
00:31:45,571 --> 00:31:46,740
You're terrible at it.

953
00:31:46,741 --> 00:31:48,140
- You have to replace him.
- Really?

954
00:31:48,141 --> 00:31:49,841
I'll show you how I succeed.

955
00:31:50,071 --> 00:31:51,780
- Jong Min is terrible at it.
- That's not true.

956
00:31:51,781 --> 00:31:53,341
Jong Min said that he'll disappoint us.

957
00:31:53,551 --> 00:31:54,611
I'll knock it down.

958
00:31:55,551 --> 00:31:56,581
What?

959
00:31:57,951 --> 00:32:01,121
(It turns out that he's an ultimate master.)

960
00:32:01,851 --> 00:32:03,320
What just happened?

961
00:32:03,321 --> 00:32:04,961
- That was nice.
- I can do it in one go.

962
00:32:04,991 --> 00:32:06,660
- It won't bounce off.
- I'll do it with affection.

963
00:32:06,661 --> 00:32:08,030
Yes, do it with affection.

964
00:32:08,031 --> 00:32:09,031
I'll start.

965
00:32:09,591 --> 00:32:10,600
All right.

966
00:32:10,601 --> 00:32:12,560
(The current time is 9:20am. They must make it this time.)

967
00:32:12,561 --> 00:32:14,701
- Please make it.
- Don't worry.

968
00:32:14,831 --> 00:32:15,900
That's right.

969
00:32:15,901 --> 00:32:17,421
- We knocked down one.
- That's right.

970
00:32:17,701 --> 00:32:19,470
(They're off to a good start.)

971
00:32:19,471 --> 00:32:20,710
We definitely have a chance.

972
00:32:20,711 --> 00:32:21,970
We have three tries.

973
00:32:21,971 --> 00:32:24,210
- We have three tries left.
- Isn't it too far to the left?

974
00:32:24,211 --> 00:32:25,741
Shouldn't it be in the middle?

975
00:32:26,311 --> 00:32:27,781
- I'll start.
- Let's go.

976
00:32:28,311 --> 00:32:29,710
Yes.

977
00:32:29,711 --> 00:32:31,581
(Gasping)

978
00:32:31,921 --> 00:32:32,981
Let's go.

979
00:32:33,221 --> 00:32:38,121
(The table tennis ball falls off neatly.)

980
00:32:39,461 --> 00:32:42,631
(Seon Ho survives without getting covered with flour.)

981
00:32:42,831 --> 00:32:44,200
(They passed Infinite Flour Nightmare Round 2.)

982
00:32:44,201 --> 00:32:46,731
We'll move onto the third round.

983
00:32:47,001 --> 00:32:48,900
- All right, everyone.
- It's the final round.

984
00:32:48,901 --> 00:32:50,170
(The long-awaited final round)

985
00:32:50,171 --> 00:32:51,541
Mission Round Three.

986
00:32:51,741 --> 00:32:53,171
It's Guess Odd or Even Tangerine.

987
00:32:53,401 --> 00:32:54,470
- Odd or Even Tangerine?
- Odd or Even Tangerine.

988
00:32:54,471 --> 00:32:55,540
(The name indicates that it's a game of luck.)

989
00:32:55,541 --> 00:32:56,570
This will be about luck.

990
00:32:56,571 --> 00:32:57,811
It's literally a game of luck.

991
00:32:57,981 --> 00:32:59,501
The number of tangerine pieces inside?

992
00:33:00,081 --> 00:33:02,880
Guess if the number of tangerine pieces is even or odd.

993
00:33:02,881 --> 00:33:03,980
- Is there one player?
- Yes.

994
00:33:03,981 --> 00:33:06,750
We can keep trying while one person gets the flour shower.

995
00:33:06,751 --> 00:33:08,271
Peel the tangerine after saying "odd."

996
00:33:08,321 --> 00:33:09,820
What are you doing? Hurry up and go.

997
00:33:09,821 --> 00:33:11,760
- I was sitting down a moment ago.
- I know,

998
00:33:11,761 --> 00:33:13,160
but it didn't pop. You have to stay there.

999
00:33:13,161 --> 00:33:15,130
Can they come up with rules however they want?

1000
00:33:15,131 --> 00:33:16,131
- That's how it is.
- Don't you feel...

1001
00:33:16,132 --> 00:33:17,531
motivated to be like them?

1002
00:33:17,631 --> 00:33:18,800
Look at their faces.

1003
00:33:18,801 --> 00:33:20,030
Don't you want to be funny too?

1004
00:33:20,031 --> 00:33:21,071
(Variety show snowmen)

1005
00:33:21,271 --> 00:33:23,031
(Tempted)

1006
00:33:23,131 --> 00:33:24,470
- I'm feeling lucky today.
- Go.

1007
00:33:24,471 --> 00:33:25,601
- That's great.
- Okay.

1008
00:33:25,841 --> 00:33:26,940
He's bold.

1009
00:33:26,941 --> 00:33:28,971
- By the way, this is easy.
- I know.

1010
00:33:29,641 --> 00:33:31,381
The one I peeled was this big.

1011
00:33:33,581 --> 00:33:34,710
- Even.
- Odd.

1012
00:33:34,711 --> 00:33:35,910
- Is it even?
- It's even.

1013
00:33:35,911 --> 00:33:37,180
- Your guess is even.
- Yes.

1014
00:33:37,181 --> 00:33:38,751
- My guess is odd.
- Yes.

1015
00:33:38,851 --> 00:33:41,091
- This time, it's even.
- Okay.

1016
00:33:41,321 --> 00:33:42,920
Team 2 Days 1 Night's guess is even.

1017
00:33:42,921 --> 00:33:44,620
I have a good feeling about Jong Min.

1018
00:33:44,621 --> 00:33:46,360
Let's find out. I don't think it's correct.

