1770
00:57:33,282 --> 00:57:34,882
Shall we get going now?

1771
00:57:35,412 --> 00:57:38,051
- Let's eat some first.
- Let's eat some.

1772
00:57:38,052 --> 00:57:39,821
- Let's taste it.
- What flavors do you want?

1773
00:57:39,822 --> 00:57:42,252
- Strawberry and vanilla.
- Strawberry and vanilla?

1774
00:57:42,652 --> 00:57:43,951
(It's almost like a rock.)

1775
00:57:43,952 --> 00:57:45,062
It's frozen.

1776
00:57:47,362 --> 00:57:50,562
I think we'll have to melt it first.

1777
00:57:51,302 --> 00:57:53,102
Wouldn't it melt on the way?

1778
00:57:53,432 --> 00:57:55,532
Let's go up.

1779
00:57:56,002 --> 00:57:57,642
It's over here. Why are you going there?

1780
00:57:58,302 --> 00:57:59,371
Hurry up!

1781
00:57:59,372 --> 00:58:01,442
Hurry up? You didn't ride the bike so much.

1782
00:58:01,742 --> 00:58:03,272
I rode the bike for 8km.

1783
00:58:04,142 --> 00:58:05,442
Hurry up!

1784
00:58:05,942 --> 00:58:08,612
(I guess I should run.)

1785
00:58:09,412 --> 00:58:10,512
What is this?

1786
00:58:10,882 --> 00:58:13,251
(He finds...)

1787
00:58:13,252 --> 00:58:14,621
Give me hotteok.

1788
00:58:14,622 --> 00:58:15,622
(a stall?)

1789
00:58:16,052 --> 00:58:17,992
(This place...)

1790
00:58:18,762 --> 00:58:21,761
You arrived at Jangja Island famous for its hotteok street.

1791
00:58:21,762 --> 00:58:23,691
(Jangja Island is the smallest inhabited island...)

1792
00:58:23,692 --> 00:58:25,632
(in the Gogunsan Islands.)

1793
00:58:25,732 --> 00:58:27,852
The mission for the three of you who chose hotteok...

1794
00:58:27,932 --> 00:58:30,132
is Three Winter Snacks Random Game.

1795
00:58:31,202 --> 00:58:34,972
You will choose one...

1796
00:58:35,242 --> 00:58:36,842
among hotteok, fishcake, and coffee.

1797
00:58:37,442 --> 00:58:40,012
If everyone picks successfully, the mission will end.

1798
00:58:40,342 --> 00:58:42,711
If even one of you fails, you can reattempt...

1799
00:58:42,712 --> 00:58:44,621
- But...
- after five minutes.

1800
00:58:44,622 --> 00:58:47,452
One has to choose coffee,

1801
00:58:47,822 --> 00:58:49,191
- one has to choose fishcake, - One person.

1802
00:58:49,192 --> 00:58:50,621
And one has to choose hotteok?

1803
00:58:50,622 --> 00:58:51,821
Okay. I'll choose hotteok.

1804
00:58:51,822 --> 00:58:53,398
- I'll get the fishcake.
- I'll get hotteok.

1805
00:58:53,422 --> 00:58:54,491
What?

1806
00:58:54,492 --> 00:58:55,761
Play rock-paper-scissors.

1807
00:58:55,762 --> 00:58:58,362
He can't drink coffee. Choose it for him.

1808
00:58:58,602 --> 00:58:59,902
But he wants hotteok.

1809
00:59:00,002 --> 00:59:01,132
I'll take the fishcake then.

1810
00:59:01,332 --> 00:59:02,531
Take the fishcake.

1811
00:59:02,532 --> 00:59:03,701
You're good at this.

1812
00:59:03,702 --> 00:59:04,771
- Right.
- We're not.

1813
00:59:04,772 --> 00:59:07,041
- I can't drink coffee.
- Take the coffee for us.

1814
00:59:07,042 --> 00:59:08,171
Okay.

1815
00:59:08,172 --> 00:59:09,618
- Okay.
- I'll give you some fishcake.

1816
00:59:09,642 --> 00:59:12,141
- I can switch with you later.
- If you get the real hotteok,

1817
00:59:12,142 --> 00:59:13,882
- give me a bite.
- Yes. We can share.

1818
00:59:14,042 --> 00:59:15,681
Hurry up!

1819
00:59:15,682 --> 00:59:16,912
Let's do it quickly.

1820
00:59:17,552 --> 00:59:21,152
(Honey hotteok versus capsaicin hotteok)

1821
00:59:22,152 --> 00:59:24,262
(It's a 1 in 2 chance.)

1822
00:59:24,822 --> 00:59:25,991
- Hotteok.
- Hotteok?

1823
00:59:25,992 --> 00:59:27,368
(Seon Ho is in charge of the random fishcake game.)

1824
00:59:27,392 --> 00:59:29,661
(Normal fishcake versus salt fishcake)

1825
00:59:29,662 --> 00:59:31,202
- I really can't tell.
- Yes.

1826
00:59:32,632 --> 00:59:34,571
- They look the same.
- Don't look at it from so close.

1827
00:59:34,572 --> 00:59:36,031
Don't cross the black line.

1828
00:59:36,032 --> 00:59:37,871
(Americano versus sand lance coffee)

1829
00:59:37,872 --> 00:59:39,972
(It's also a 1 in 2 chance.)

1830
00:59:40,402 --> 00:59:42,871
(The chances of succeeding is 1 in 8!)

1831
00:59:42,872 --> 00:59:45,111
(An extremely difficult mission)

1832
00:59:45,112 --> 00:59:47,281
It looks the same. You did a great job.

1833
00:59:47,282 --> 00:59:48,282
You did it well.

1834
00:59:48,283 --> 00:59:51,221
One of them is pressed and the other one isn't.

1835
00:59:51,222 --> 00:59:52,921
One of mine is dry and the other one is moist.

1836
00:59:52,922 --> 00:59:54,891
Would it be the pressed one...

1837
00:59:54,892 --> 00:59:57,351
If there are three options,

1838
00:59:57,352 --> 01:00:00,021
the one that stands out can be removed.

1839
01:00:00,022 --> 01:00:01,162
This is more confusing.

1840
01:00:01,892 --> 01:00:03,261
(Having 2 options is harder...)

1841
01:00:03,262 --> 01:00:04,601
(because there's nothing to compare them to.)

1842
01:00:04,602 --> 01:00:06,701
- Let's guess it.
- I'll start.

1843
01:00:06,702 --> 01:00:07,971
- I'll start.
- Okay.

1844
01:00:07,972 --> 01:00:09,832
- I'll go.
- Okay. You can go one at a time.

1845
01:00:10,132 --> 01:00:11,741
I'll start. The first one!

1846
01:00:11,742 --> 01:00:12,742
Okay.

1847
01:00:12,743 --> 01:00:14,472
(He chooses the slightly pressed hotteok.)

1848
01:00:15,012 --> 01:00:17,512
(He takes a bite right away.)

1849
01:00:17,572 --> 01:00:18,611
It's the right one.

1850
01:00:18,612 --> 01:00:20,012
(It's honey!)

1851
01:00:20,442 --> 01:00:22,181
(He found the honey hotteok in the first attempt.)

1852
01:00:22,182 --> 01:00:23,581
- Success!
- Let me have a bite.

1853
01:00:23,582 --> 01:00:25,482
- I won't finish it.
- Don't eat it.

1854
01:00:25,682 --> 01:00:27,921
One is moist and the other is dry. Should I just pick?

1855
01:00:27,922 --> 01:00:29,622
- Just go.
- You can't tell.

1856
01:00:30,152 --> 01:00:32,761
- Okay. Take a big bite.
- What's...

1857
01:00:32,762 --> 01:00:34,261
I don't know. I'll just pick.

1858
01:00:34,262 --> 01:00:35,862
Let's end this at once!

1859
01:00:36,532 --> 01:00:38,901
(Did Seon Ho pick the tasty fishcake?)

1860
01:00:38,902 --> 01:00:41,001
It's the right one.

1861
01:00:41,002 --> 01:00:42,432
- Success.
- Let's exchange.

1862
01:00:43,372 --> 01:00:45,902
(Jong Min is the only one left!)

1863
01:00:46,242 --> 01:00:48,402
(They're exchanging their food they picked correctly.)

1864
01:00:48,812 --> 01:00:50,641
(This decides the mission's result and their snacks.)

1865
01:00:50,642 --> 01:00:52,412
It's really similar.

1866
01:00:53,042 --> 01:00:54,081
It's really similar.

1867
01:00:54,082 --> 01:00:55,802
(The expert in random games also approves.)

1868
01:00:56,052 --> 01:00:57,952
We're doing well now.

1869
01:00:58,782 --> 01:01:00,722
One of them is sticky.

1870
01:01:01,052 --> 01:01:02,351
One isn't sticky.

1871
01:01:02,352 --> 01:01:03,991
(One sloshes and doesn't look sticky.)

1872
01:01:03,992 --> 01:01:07,292
(One is still and looks sticky.)

1873
01:01:07,322 --> 01:01:08,761
Shouldn't you pick the one that's not sticky?

1874
01:01:08,762 --> 01:01:10,208
I'll go with the one that's not sticky.

1875
01:01:10,232 --> 01:01:11,431
(The one that's not sticky according to Jong Min)

1876
01:01:11,432 --> 01:01:13,161
Okay. Please take a big sip.

1877
01:01:13,162 --> 01:01:14,331
- I'll start.
- Okay.

1878
01:01:14,332 --> 01:01:15,612
(It's time to check the result.)

1879
01:01:17,372 --> 01:01:19,141
(Frowning)

1880
01:01:19,142 --> 01:01:21,012
- It's the right one.
- No.

1881
01:01:21,642 --> 01:01:22,711
(Jong Min's expression even confuses the members.)

1882
01:01:22,712 --> 01:01:24,242
That's...

1883
01:01:25,342 --> 01:01:26,911
(Which is it?)

1884
01:01:26,912 --> 01:01:28,381
- He'll spit it out.
- It's the right one.

1885
01:01:28,382 --> 01:01:29,482
(Swallowing?)

1886
01:01:30,052 --> 01:01:31,052
(Did we succeed?)

1887
01:01:31,052 --> 01:01:32,052
What?

1888
01:01:32,682 --> 01:01:34,821
(He's very flustered.)

1889
01:01:34,822 --> 01:01:35,822
Really?

1890
01:01:36,552 --> 01:01:38,061
- Really?
- You succeeded.

1891
01:01:38,062 --> 01:01:39,062
Is this real?

1892
01:01:39,063 --> 01:01:41,792
You all succeeded the Three Winter Snacks Random Game.

1893
01:01:41,892 --> 01:01:43,332
We succeeded so easily.

1894
01:01:43,992 --> 01:01:45,332
- Really?
- Are we done?

1895
01:01:45,732 --> 01:01:47,461
How did we do it at once?

1896
01:01:47,462 --> 01:01:48,771
The chances of succeeding...

1897
01:01:48,772 --> 01:01:50,601
We did so well. We're done.

1898
01:01:50,602 --> 01:01:52,701
- It was so light.
- It's 11:16am.

1899
01:01:52,702 --> 01:01:55,041
Are we done with the game?

1900
01:01:55,042 --> 01:01:56,541
The other team...

1901
01:01:56,542 --> 01:01:58,581
also has to succeed.

1902
01:01:58,582 --> 01:01:59,582
Let's wait.

1903
01:01:59,583 --> 01:02:01,351
Since you succeeded,

1904
01:02:01,352 --> 01:02:02,581
- Let's go.
- let's wait in the car.

1905
01:02:02,582 --> 01:02:03,712
- Okay.
- That's nice.

1906
01:02:04,252 --> 01:02:05,322
Where did they go?

1907
01:02:05,352 --> 01:02:06,752
They should also finish it quickly.

1908
01:02:07,352 --> 01:02:09,651
Why is it so steep?

1909
01:02:09,652 --> 01:02:10,992
(They just began hiking.)

1910
01:02:12,462 --> 01:02:15,132
Who sells ice cream in January?

1911
01:02:16,162 --> 01:02:18,762
Who eats ice cream...

1912
01:02:19,362 --> 01:02:20,831
in January on a mountain?

1913
01:02:20,832 --> 01:02:22,272
(They'll have to eat it themselves.)

1914
01:02:23,372 --> 01:02:30,042
(They also haven't met anyone during the hike so far.)

1915
01:02:31,182 --> 01:02:33,811
(They kept on going up...)

1916
01:02:33,812 --> 01:02:36,282
(and up again.)

1917
01:02:37,952 --> 01:02:41,152
(Nobody in sight)

1918
01:02:41,392 --> 01:02:43,651
This is the kind of day I should have lost 3kg.

1919
01:02:43,652 --> 01:02:44,932
(But there is a bigger problem.)

1920
01:02:45,262 --> 01:02:46,361
Gosh, this is tough.

1921
01:02:46,362 --> 01:02:49,562
(The ice cream is too heavy, and the mountain is too steep.)

1922
01:02:50,262 --> 01:02:54,332
(They can't stop moaning even at Daejang Peak.)

1923
01:02:54,832 --> 01:02:55,832
All right.

1924
01:02:57,132 --> 01:02:58,442
Let me have another bite.

1925
01:02:59,472 --> 01:03:02,772
(It's 11:47am.)

1926
01:03:03,772 --> 01:03:09,482
(It looks like the two of them have to finish the ice cream.)

1927
01:03:10,552 --> 01:03:13,721
(They pulled themselves together and continued the climb.)

1928
01:03:13,722 --> 01:03:14,922
I'm exhausted.

1929
01:03:16,622 --> 01:03:18,361
(There's no one around, and it's just exhausting.)

1930
01:03:18,362 --> 01:03:20,291
Ice cream here!

1931
01:03:20,292 --> 01:03:22,292
(There's no one around, and it's just exhausting.)

1932
01:03:22,462 --> 01:03:25,902
(A murmur of voices)

1933
01:03:26,462 --> 01:03:27,801
Scoop the ice cream.

1934
01:03:27,802 --> 01:03:29,272
It's a group! Let's sell it.

1935
01:03:30,372 --> 01:03:33,802
(It's a group?)

1936
01:03:33,972 --> 01:03:35,712
- Hello.
- Hi, everyone.

1937
01:03:36,442 --> 01:03:38,081
- Nice to meet you.
- We have ice cream here.

1938
01:03:38,082 --> 01:03:39,311
Here is your ice cream.

1939
01:03:39,312 --> 01:03:40,811
- Ice cream for you.
- Do we have to work on quizzes?

1940
01:03:40,812 --> 01:03:42,481
If you want to get ice cream,

1941
01:03:42,482 --> 01:03:44,211
- please line up here.
- You can queue up.

1942
01:03:44,212 --> 01:03:45,822
Please queue up in one line.

1943
01:03:45,922 --> 01:03:47,581
Here is your ice cream.

1944
01:03:47,582 --> 01:03:49,951
We have strawberry, vanilla, and chocolate. It's random.

1945
01:03:49,952 --> 01:03:51,661
- You can't pick the flavors.
- Goodness.

1946
01:03:51,662 --> 01:03:53,522
What brings you here with your friends?

1947
01:03:54,062 --> 01:03:56,091
- We're from a hiking club.
- I see, a hiking club.

1948
01:03:56,092 --> 01:03:57,661
A hiking club with history and tradition!

1949
01:03:57,662 --> 01:03:58,801
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

1950
01:03:58,802 --> 01:03:59,802
Let's go, Hiking Club.

1951
01:03:59,803 --> 01:04:01,061
You can walk down this way one by one.

1952
01:04:01,062 --> 01:04:02,601
- Thank you.
- Thank you for the ice cream.

1953
01:04:02,602 --> 01:04:03,772
Next one in line.

1954
01:04:03,972 --> 01:04:06,272
- It's lovely.
- Please introduce yourself.

1955
01:04:06,572 --> 01:04:07,801
- Here.
- Come here.

1956
01:04:07,802 --> 01:04:09,942
You have great energy.

1957
01:04:10,012 --> 01:04:11,511
How long have you been hiking?

1958
01:04:11,512 --> 01:04:13,081
- It has been 10 years.
- What, 10 years?

1959
01:04:13,082 --> 01:04:15,052
You're an expert then.

1960
01:04:16,112 --> 01:04:18,128
Please send a video message to your beloved family.

1961
01:04:18,152 --> 01:04:19,782
- He's not married.
- He's not?

1962
01:04:19,822 --> 01:04:21,392
- He's not married.
- He's not?

1963
01:04:21,992 --> 01:04:24,021
Really? That's amazing.

1964
01:04:24,022 --> 01:04:25,761
I thought he was married.

1965
01:04:25,762 --> 01:04:27,338
I hope girls from all over Korea give him a call.

1966
01:04:27,362 --> 01:04:29,262
- Please scoop a lot.
- Sure, thank you.

1967
01:04:29,362 --> 01:04:31,501
- Gosh, it's all gone.
- Okay, here you go.

1968
01:04:31,502 --> 01:04:34,061
- Strawberry ice cream for you.
- Thank you.

1969
01:04:34,062 --> 01:04:35,131
Well...

1970
01:04:35,132 --> 01:04:36,731
(Giving ice cream to about 20 people in groups)

1971
01:04:36,732 --> 01:04:37,941
We shared all the ice cream.

1972
01:04:37,942 --> 01:04:40,041
- Great.
- Okay.

1973
01:04:40,042 --> 01:04:41,271
Thank you.

1974
01:04:41,272 --> 01:04:42,611
We got rid of about one-third of the ice cream.

1975
01:04:42,612 --> 01:04:44,988
(They got rid of about 40 percent of the ice cream in no time.)

1976
01:04:45,012 --> 01:04:46,511
(It's 11:59am.)

1977
01:04:46,512 --> 01:04:49,912
(Time is slipping away mercilessly.)

1978
01:04:50,152 --> 01:04:51,551
We're almost done, let's go.

1979
01:04:51,552 --> 01:04:52,751
- Let's go.
- Let's do this.

1980
01:04:52,752 --> 01:04:54,422
(It's still a long way to go.)

1981
01:04:54,622 --> 01:04:57,652
It's as steep as Stairway to the Sky.

1982
01:04:58,092 --> 01:04:59,491
This is so challenging.

1983
01:04:59,492 --> 01:05:01,861
(The stairs are very steep.)

1984
01:05:01,862 --> 01:05:03,292
Look at how steep these are.

1985
01:05:03,532 --> 01:05:05,032
It feels like summer.

1986
01:05:05,762 --> 01:05:07,702
I want to take off my sweater.

1987
01:05:07,932 --> 01:05:09,032
Do you want to take it off?

1988
01:05:09,502 --> 01:05:10,801
Isn't it that hot?

1989
01:05:10,802 --> 01:05:12,142
Right. It's driving me crazy.

1990
01:05:12,872 --> 01:05:17,572
(In hopes of seeing more people at the top)

1991
01:05:19,042 --> 01:05:23,252
(How many people will be waiting to welcome them at the top?)

1992
01:05:24,722 --> 01:05:25,882
I don't see anything.

1993
01:05:26,652 --> 01:05:28,122
This is not the peak.

1994
01:05:28,992 --> 01:05:30,622
What is this?

1995
01:05:31,052 --> 01:05:32,762
I can't see anything at all.

1996
01:05:32,862 --> 01:05:34,161
This can't be the peak.

1997
01:05:34,162 --> 01:05:36,042
(They can see neither the people nor the view.)

1998
01:05:36,162 --> 01:05:37,232
It's the top...

1999
01:05:37,692 --> 01:05:38,761
What is this?

2000
01:05:38,762 --> 01:05:40,802
How can we sell ice cream here?

2001
01:05:44,132 --> 01:05:45,301
What is this?

2002
01:05:45,302 --> 01:05:47,641
(It's only the production crew at the top.)

2003
01:05:47,642 --> 01:05:48,642
How can we...

2004
01:05:48,643 --> 01:05:50,241
- Hey!
- I see more people.

2005
01:05:50,242 --> 01:05:52,411
- Hey, girl.
- Which flavor do you want?

2006
01:05:52,412 --> 01:05:53,842
- Hello.
- Hello, girl.

2007
01:05:54,142 --> 01:05:55,681
How old are you? Are you in the 7th or 8th grade?

2008
01:05:55,682 --> 01:05:57,581
I'm a seventh grader.

2009
01:05:57,582 --> 01:05:59,721
- Right.
- I see.

2010
01:05:59,722 --> 01:06:01,221
Strawberry, chocolate, or vanilla?

2011
01:06:01,222 --> 01:06:02,551
- I want vanilla.
- Okay.

2012
01:06:02,552 --> 01:06:04,591
- Vanilla, you got it.
- Great.

2013
01:06:04,592 --> 01:06:06,961
- You're so tall and pretty.
- Thank you.

2014
01:06:06,962 --> 01:06:08,192
I mean it.

2015
01:06:08,632 --> 01:06:10,692
You must be close to your parents.

2016
01:06:10,762 --> 01:06:12,062
Puberty still hasn't shown up?

2017
01:06:13,662 --> 01:06:16,002
- No?
- I don't think it's here yet.

2018
01:06:16,532 --> 01:06:18,071
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

2019
01:06:18,072 --> 01:06:19,171
All right, bye.

2020
01:06:19,172 --> 01:06:20,372
Congratulations.

2021
01:06:20,772 --> 01:06:21,811
Let's go, guys.

2022
01:06:21,812 --> 01:06:23,341
Thank you, she's cute.

2023
01:06:23,342 --> 01:06:24,371
Bye.

2024
01:06:24,372 --> 01:06:26,112
- Bye.
- Be careful when you go down.

2025
01:06:26,982 --> 01:06:29,112
Raise your hand if you want to have ice cream.

2026
