- You did that thing.

2620
01:26:13,030 --> 01:26:15,230
With mayonnaise.

2621
01:26:15,330 --> 01:26:16,530
- Really?
- That sounds great.

2622
01:26:17,000 --> 01:26:18,970
- We will be grateful to get it.
- Just one crab.

2623
01:26:19,600 --> 01:26:20,669
- This is garlic.
- Okay.

2624
01:26:20,670 --> 01:26:21,699
(What game are they playing to get a grilled crab?)

2625
01:26:21,700 --> 01:26:24,469
Guess how many cloves this garlic has.

2626
01:26:24,470 --> 01:26:25,539
(Guess the number of garlic cloves!)

2627
01:26:25,540 --> 01:26:27,420
- The one who guesses correctly...
- It's hard.

2628
01:26:27,580 --> 01:26:29,479
Can we answer? Take a guess.

2629
01:26:29,480 --> 01:26:30,510
I bet it's 11.

2630
01:26:30,680 --> 01:26:31,850
- Eleven?
- Nine.

2631
01:26:32,480 --> 01:26:34,120
- Ten.
- Eight.

2632
01:26:34,780 --> 01:26:35,850
Twelve.

2633
01:26:36,650 --> 01:26:38,130
- Okay.
- I guess one of us is right.

2634
01:26:38,490 --> 01:26:41,090
Cut the garlic with a knife and check the number.

2635
01:26:41,390 --> 01:26:43,060
- Please.
- Please.

2636
01:26:43,760 --> 01:26:45,230
There aren't as many as we thought.

2637
01:26:45,800 --> 01:26:47,859
- Two each.
- One, two, three, four,

2638
01:26:47,860 --> 01:26:50,600
- five, six, seven, eight, nine.
- I bet it's ten.

2639
01:26:50,830 --> 01:26:52,070
Nine.

2640
01:26:52,400 --> 01:26:53,400
Ten.

2641
01:26:53,540 --> 01:26:54,570
Ten!

2642
01:26:55,340 --> 01:26:57,440
(Lee Joon wins.)

2643
01:26:57,770 --> 01:26:59,339
(Touched)

2644
01:26:59,340 --> 01:27:00,410
Joon!

2645
01:27:00,980 --> 01:27:02,780
It could've been nine.

2646
01:27:03,150 --> 01:27:04,350
It has ten cloves.

2647
01:27:05,050 --> 01:27:06,950
I love crabs.

2648
01:27:07,450 --> 01:27:09,250
You're lucky.

2649
01:27:10,090 --> 01:27:12,620
(The 2026 feel-good guy, Lee Joon gets a crab.)

2650
01:27:13,720 --> 01:27:15,560
The main dish is here.

2651
01:27:16,060 --> 01:27:18,530
It looks delicious. Open it with your hands and eat it.

2652
01:27:18,690 --> 01:27:20,699
This is a dish for me.

2653
01:27:20,700 --> 01:27:22,199
- Yes.
- A dish for me.

2654
01:27:22,200 --> 01:27:23,869
I love crabs.

2655
01:27:23,870 --> 01:27:25,569
- You do?
- Ta-da.

2656
01:27:25,570 --> 01:27:27,240
(He can't hold back his smile.)

2657
01:27:27,740 --> 01:27:29,439
(Grilled meaty crab with a lot of mayonnaise on it)

2658
01:27:29,440 --> 01:27:30,569
It must be tender.

2659
01:27:30,570 --> 01:27:31,709
Do you eat the crab shell?

2660
01:27:31,710 --> 01:27:32,710
- I do.
- Really?

2661
01:27:32,711 --> 01:27:34,209
- That's the best part.
- I didn't think you'd eat it.

2662
01:27:34,210 --> 01:27:35,526
(He fails to steal the crab shell.)

2663
01:27:35,550 --> 01:27:36,979
- Squeeze it out.
- Mayonnaise.

2664
01:27:36,980 --> 01:27:38,819
(He finally tries the grilled crab with mayonnaise.)

2665
01:27:38,820 --> 01:27:40,349
It must have a mild taste.

2666
01:27:40,350 --> 01:27:41,956
(He finally tries the grilled crab with mayonnaise.)

2667
01:27:41,980 --> 01:27:43,289
(How does it taste?)

2668
01:27:43,290 --> 01:27:44,350
How is it?

2669
01:27:45,350 --> 01:27:46,559
This is really good.

2670
01:27:46,560 --> 01:27:48,159
- It must be good.
- It's so delicious.

2671
01:27:48,160 --> 01:27:50,060
- Really?
- It's not greasy at all.

2672
01:27:50,230 --> 01:27:51,689
- Of course not.
- This is...

2673
01:27:51,690 --> 01:27:53,700
This tastes like a fancy dish.

2674
01:27:54,360 --> 01:27:55,999
Like something cooked by a chef.

2675
01:27:56,000 --> 01:27:57,569
- Really?
- This is really...

2676
01:27:57,570 --> 01:27:58,599
Is it amazing?

2677
01:27:58,600 --> 01:27:59,999
It has a smoky flavor.

2678
01:28:00,000 --> 01:28:01,769
- Of course.
- I really like it.

2679
01:28:01,770 --> 01:28:03,409
- Does it have a smoky flavor?
- It does.

2680
01:28:03,410 --> 01:28:06,210
Try the crab shell. That's it.

2681
01:28:06,480 --> 01:28:08,510
It's really good with mayonnaise.

2682
01:28:08,980 --> 01:28:11,810
If you are not going to eat it, can we have it?

2683
01:28:11,880 --> 01:28:15,490
You are not going to eat the legs, are you?

2684
01:28:15,590 --> 01:28:16,789
I won't eat the legs.

2685
01:28:16,790 --> 01:28:18,549
- Do you want this?
- We could have one leg.

2686
01:28:18,550 --> 01:28:19,759
Right. Let us eat the claw.

2687
01:28:19,760 --> 01:28:21,220
Let us eat the claw.

2688
01:28:21,660 --> 01:28:23,130
I have nine cloves here.

2689
01:28:23,430 --> 01:28:25,559
- Nine cloves.
- Guess how many I'm holding.

2690
01:28:25,560 --> 01:28:26,630
Okay.

2691
01:28:28,230 --> 01:28:30,629
- Don't look at his hands.
- Why not?

2692
01:28:30,630 --> 01:28:31,999
If you look at his hands, you can tell how many he has.

2693
01:28:32,000 --> 01:28:33,340
I'm shuffling.

2694
01:28:33,840 --> 01:28:34,899
Make a guess.

2695
01:28:34,900 --> 01:28:37,010
(How many cloves is Joon holding in his hand?)

2696
01:28:37,410 --> 01:28:38,770
I'll go with two.

2697
01:28:39,640 --> 01:28:41,340
- Three.
- One.

2698
01:28:42,510 --> 01:28:43,949
I have no choice. Two.

2699
01:28:43,950 --> 01:28:46,220
No. If I were you, I'd say "None."

2700
01:28:46,780 --> 01:28:48,020
Will you go with that?

2701
01:28:48,180 --> 01:28:49,549
- Jong Min.
- I'll go with zero.

2702
01:28:49,550 --> 01:28:50,719
- I'll go with two.
- I'll go with zero.

2703
01:28:50,720 --> 01:28:52,159
- I'll go with two.
- Two?

2704
01:28:52,160 --> 01:28:53,520
- Yes.
- Three.

2705
01:28:53,720 --> 01:28:54,890
- One.
- Okay.

2706
01:28:55,190 --> 01:28:57,059
- The answer is...
- Do we have a winner?

2707
01:28:57,060 --> 01:28:58,189
We do have a winner.

2708
01:28:58,190 --> 01:28:59,460
- Okay.
- All right.

2709
01:28:59,830 --> 01:29:00,929
The answer is...

2710
01:29:00,930 --> 01:29:01,959
Two.

2711
01:29:01,960 --> 01:29:03,529
- Zero!
- Two!

2712
01:29:03,530 --> 01:29:04,600
- It must be one.
- Three.

2713
01:29:04,900 --> 01:29:05,939
(All eyes are focused on Joon's hand.)

2714
01:29:05,940 --> 01:29:07,240
- There's none.
- One.

2715
01:29:07,570 --> 01:29:08,870
- One.
- One.

2716
01:29:09,170 --> 01:29:10,509
- You're over.
- Okay.

2717
01:29:10,510 --> 01:29:11,709
- That might be it.
- One.

2718
01:29:11,710 --> 01:29:13,409
- Okay.
- I'm the winner for now.

2719
01:29:13,410 --> 01:29:14,479
Two.

2720
01:29:14,480 --> 01:29:16,550
- That's it.
- Two.

2721
01:29:17,350 --> 01:29:19,250
It's two. Jong Min was right.

2722
01:29:19,750 --> 01:29:20,920
- Two!
- What?

2723
01:29:21,380 --> 01:29:23,190
(Se Yoon, who said 1, is out.)

2724
01:29:23,350 --> 01:29:25,120
There's more. It's three.

2725
01:29:25,760 --> 01:29:27,289
- I'm sure there's one more.
- That might be it.

2726
01:29:27,290 --> 01:29:28,319
It's three.

2727
01:29:28,320 --> 01:29:30,160
(One of these two will get the claw.)

2728
01:29:30,190 --> 01:29:31,229
It's three.

2729
01:29:31,230 --> 01:29:32,400
I'm sure there's one more.

2730
01:29:33,900 --> 01:29:35,360
Yes! It's two!

2731
01:29:35,600 --> 01:29:38,070
(DinDin wins.)

2732
01:29:38,400 --> 01:29:40,199
(He takes the claw of victory.)

2733
01:29:40,200 --> 01:29:41,299
Was it Jong Min's answer?

2734
01:29:41,300 --> 01:29:43,009
- Yes.
- He suddenly said zero.

2735
01:29:43,010 --> 01:29:44,039
Nice.

2736
01:29:44,040 --> 01:29:45,339
(The fates of the two people changed in an instant.)

2737
01:29:45,340 --> 01:29:46,980
I shouldn't have said that.

2738
01:29:48,010 --> 01:29:53,220
(He puts the precious claw quickly into his mouth.)

2739
01:29:53,550 --> 01:29:54,950
It tastes like butter-grilled crab.

2740
01:29:57,320 --> 01:29:59,819
(The hard-earned leg)

2741
01:29:59,820 --> 01:30:01,189
It's quite meaty.

2742
01:30:01,190 --> 01:30:02,590
Yes. It's not bad.

2743
01:30:03,630 --> 01:30:05,260
I got this much meat.

2744
01:30:05,760 --> 01:30:07,030
- My gosh.
- That's a lot.

2745
01:30:08,260 --> 01:30:09,740
You did a good job removing the meat.

2746
01:30:12,270 --> 01:30:13,400
I'm tired.

2747
01:30:14,170 --> 01:30:15,300
I exercised a lot.

2748
01:30:15,870 --> 01:30:16,939
I know.

2749
01:30:16,940 --> 01:30:19,879
Eating ramyeon after playing in the water makes me sleepy.

2750
01:30:19,880 --> 01:30:21,240
You're right.

2751
01:30:22,350 --> 01:30:24,709
You must feel drowsy after eating.

2752
01:30:24,710 --> 01:30:26,480
- Yes.
- I'm feeling better now.

2753
01:30:26,920 --> 01:30:30,649
Now you can go inside and get some rest.

2754
01:30:30,650 --> 01:30:32,260
- Really?
- Yes.

2755
01:30:32,390 --> 01:30:34,630
That's strange. I feel like we're being taken somewhere.

2756
01:30:34,720 --> 01:30:36,860
Will you lock the door and turn on the light?

2757
01:30:37,090 --> 01:30:38,406
They won't let us leave the room.

2758
01:30:38,430 --> 01:30:39,799
- You can just rest.
- Are you serious?

2759
01:30:39,800 --> 01:30:40,800
Yes.

2760
01:30:41,230 --> 01:30:43,229
- All right.
- Let's rest when we can.

2761
01:30:43,230 --> 01:30:44,929
- Okay.
- Thank you.

2762
01:30:44,930 --> 01:30:46,339
Thank you for the food.

2763
01:30:46,340 --> 01:30:47,740
- Thank you for the food.
- Okay.

2764
01:30:48,200 --> 01:30:49,339
Do you want me to clap?

2765
01:30:49,340 --> 01:30:52,540
(What is happening to the members?)

2766
01:30:53,080 --> 01:30:55,780
(After a hearty meal)

2767
01:30:57,550 --> 01:30:58,779
It's warm in here.

2768
01:30:58,780 --> 01:31:00,520
(It's time to enjoy some rest.)

2769
01:31:00,680 --> 01:31:01,750
(Shouting)

2770
01:31:03,320 --> 01:31:06,090
(The members are exhausted after half a day.)

2771
01:31:06,390 --> 01:31:08,220
I'm really tired today.

2772
01:31:08,860 --> 01:31:10,030
That's because...

2773
01:31:10,160 --> 01:31:11,960
we had a physical game.

2774
01:31:12,160 --> 01:31:14,599
Right. I'm exhausted.

2775
01:31:14,600 --> 01:31:15,970
Cycling takes a lot of energy.

2776
01:31:16,270 --> 01:31:22,540
(They cycled endlessly in the early morning.)

2777
01:31:23,170 --> 01:31:27,380
(They climbed a slope as steep as Mount Halla!)

2778
01:31:28,140 --> 01:31:34,380
(Today's audio was full of pants and groans.)

2779
01:31:34,680 --> 01:31:37,520
(They conquered land, air, and sea in just 4 hours.)

2780
01:31:38,390 --> 01:31:40,420
Our viewers will just adore us.

2781
01:31:40,490 --> 01:31:42,160
- Okay.
- We worked hard.

2782
01:31:43,490 --> 01:31:44,759
(Giggling)

2783
01:31:44,760 --> 01:31:46,600
Is it all good if we work hard?

2784
01:31:47,130 --> 01:31:50,130
Does everyone who works hard do well and become a star?

2785
01:31:50,700 --> 01:31:52,100
Not all who work hard succeed.

2786
01:31:52,640 --> 01:31:54,170
But all who succeeded worked hard.

2787
01:31:54,470 --> 01:31:56,209
(He acts like a big brother for once!)

2788
01:31:56,210 --> 01:31:57,470
You didn't work hard.

2789
01:31:58,810 --> 01:32:00,509
Some do the opposite.

2790
01:32:00,510 --> 01:32:01,940
You have a point.

2791
01:32:02,140 --> 01:32:04,050
What are you? Are you still unknown?

2792
01:32:04,450 --> 01:32:06,680
I'm still unknown. I'm still hungry.

2793
01:32:07,150 --> 01:32:08,820
- You and Kim Min Jong.
- Yes.

2794
01:32:08,920 --> 01:32:10,690
- I'm still hungry.
- You must try harder.

2795
01:32:11,320 --> 01:32:12,359
Yes.

2796
01:32:12,360 --> 01:32:13,790
This is nice. I want to nap.

2797
01:32:13,920 --> 01:32:15,120
Nap for a while.

2798
01:32:15,290 --> 01:32:18,760
The sea looks most marvelous right now.

2799
01:32:18,830 --> 01:32:19,830
(Yawning)

2800
01:32:21,830 --> 01:32:22,830
(Yawning)

2801
01:32:23,500 --> 01:32:24,530
Let's nap.

2802
01:32:24,930 --> 01:32:26,600
- Let's do that.
- Yes.

2803
01:32:27,100 --> 01:32:28,140
Let's nap.

2804
01:32:29,740 --> 01:32:31,710
Shall I go to the next room for a poop?

2805
01:32:32,810 --> 01:32:34,209
I can't stop farting.

2806
01:32:34,210 --> 01:32:37,610
(Se Yoon heads to the toilet after the large meal.)

2807
01:32:40,480 --> 01:32:42,890
(Pausing)

2808
01:32:43,220 --> 01:32:45,960
(He found a mission card on the floor!)

2809
01:32:48,690 --> 01:32:50,630
(What's this?)

2810
01:32:51,830 --> 01:32:54,130
(Let's take it for now.)

2811
01:32:55,030 --> 01:32:57,900
(He reads it secretively in a corner.)

2812
01:32:58,200 --> 01:33:01,140
(Taking a photo with his phone)

2813
01:33:01,370 --> 01:33:03,910
(He starts to run!)

2814
01:33:04,340 --> 01:33:05,820
Do I ride something? Can I take this?

2815
01:33:06,480 --> 01:33:09,479
(He's ready to rumble.)

2816
01:33:09,480 --> 01:33:10,550
This is awesome.

2817
01:33:10,850 --> 01:33:13,380
I only left to go to the toilet.

2818
01:33:14,920 --> 01:33:20,059
(Where is Se Yoon headed?)

2819
01:33:20,060 --> 01:33:21,960
(Next episode)

2820
01:33:22,430 --> 01:33:26,230
(They thought the race was over.)

2821
01:33:26,760 --> 01:33:30,170
(The chase is back on.)

2822
01:33:30,930 --> 01:33:33,840
(A joint search mission too!)

2823
01:33:34,540 --> 01:33:36,569
(There can only be one victor.)

2824
01:33:36,570 --> 01:33:38,370
(Who will it be?)

2825
01:33:38,710 --> 01:33:40,440
(And then...)

2826
01:33:40,910 --> 01:33:42,980
(The race continued the day after.)

2827
01:33:43,180 --> 01:33:45,080
(You are surrounded.)

2828
01:33:45,710 --> 01:33:48,950
(Now it's the police.)

2829
01:33:50,220 --> 01:33:52,489
(The chase picks up speed.)

2830
01:33:52,490 --> 01:33:54,360
(Police's camera)

2831
01:33:55,460 --> 01:33:58,130
(It's suffocating.)

2832
01:33:58,330 --> 01:34:00,360
- Where are they?
- Thirty seconds!

2833
01:34:01,100 --> 01:34:03,100
(Can they evade the police...)

2834
01:34:04,270 --> 01:34:06,740
(and stay at large?)

2835
01:34:07,740 --> 01:34:10,770
(See you next week.)
